3119static int ext4_li_info_new(void)
3120{
3121 struct ext4_lazy_init *eli = NULL;
3122
3123 eli = kzalloc(sizeof(*eli), GFP_KERNEL);
3124 if (!eli)
3125 return -ENOMEM;
3126
3127 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&eli->li_request_list);
3128 mutex_init(&eli->li_list_mtx);
3129
3130 eli->li_state |= EXT4_LAZYINIT_QUIT;
3131
3132 ext4_li_info = eli;
3133
3134 return 0;
3135}
3136
3137static struct ext4_li_request *ext4_li_request_new(struct super_block *sb,
3138 ext4_group_t start)
3139{
3140 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
3141 struct ext4_li_request *elr;
3142
3143 elr = kzalloc(sizeof(*elr), GFP_KERNEL);
3144 if (!elr)
3145 return NULL;
3146
3147 elr->lr_super = sb;
3148 elr->lr_sbi = sbi;
3149 elr->lr_next_group = start;
3150
3151 /*
3152 * Randomize first schedule time of the request to
3153 * spread the inode table initialization requests
3154 * better.
3155 */
3156 elr->lr_next_sched = jiffies + (prandom_u32() %
3157 (EXT4_DEF_LI_MAX_START_DELAY * HZ));
3158 return elr;
3159}
3160
3161int ext4_register_li_request(struct super_block *sb,
3162 ext4_group_t first_not_zeroed)
3163{
3164 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
3165 struct ext4_li_request *elr = NULL;
3166 ext4_group_t ngroups = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_groups_count;
3167 int ret = 0;
3168
3169 mutex_lock(&ext4_li_mtx);
3170 if (sbi->s_li_request != NULL) {
3171 /*
3172 * Reset timeout so it can be computed again, because
3173 * s_li_wait_mult might have changed.
3174 */
3175 sbi->s_li_request->lr_timeout = 0;
3176 goto out;
3177 }
3178
3179 if (first_not_zeroed == ngroups || sb_rdonly(sb) ||
3180 !test_opt(sb, INIT_INODE_TABLE))
3181 goto out;
3182
3183 elr = ext4_li_request_new(sb, first_not_zeroed);
3184 if (!elr) {
3185 ret = -ENOMEM;
3186 goto out;
3187 }
3188
3189 if (NULL == ext4_li_info) {
3190 ret = ext4_li_info_new();
3191 if (ret)
3192 goto out;
3193 }
3194
3195 mutex_lock(&ext4_li_info->li_list_mtx);
3196 list_add(&elr->lr_request, &ext4_li_info->li_request_list);
3197 mutex_unlock(&ext4_li_info->li_list_mtx);
3198
3199 sbi->s_li_request = elr;
3200 /*
3201 * set elr to NULL here since it has been inserted to
3202 * the request_list and the removal and free of it is
3203 * handled by ext4_clear_request_list from now on.
3204 */
3205 elr = NULL;
3206
3207 if (!(ext4_li_info->li_state & EXT4_LAZYINIT_RUNNING)) {
3208 ret = ext4_run_lazyinit_thread();
3209 if (ret)
3210 goto out;
3211 }
3212out:
3213 mutex_unlock(&ext4_li_mtx);
3214 if (ret)
3215 kfree(elr);
3216 return ret;
3217}
3218
3219/*
3220 * We do not need to lock anything since this is called on
3221 * module unload.
3222 */
3223static void ext4_destroy_lazyinit_thread(void)
3224{
3225 /*
3226 * If thread exited earlier
3227 * there's nothing to be done.
3228 */
3229 if (!ext4_li_info || !ext4_lazyinit_task)
3230 return;
3231
3232 kthread_stop(ext4_lazyinit_task);
3233}

3235static int set_journal_csum_feature_set(struct super_block *sb)
3236{
3237 int ret = 1;
3238 int compat, incompat;
3239 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
3240
3241 if (ext4_has_metadata_csum(sb)) {
3242 /* journal checksum v3 */
3243 compat = 0;
3244 incompat = JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_CSUM_V3;
3245 } else {
3246 /* journal checksum v1 */
3247 compat = JBD2_FEATURE_COMPAT_CHECKSUM;
3248 incompat = 0;
3249 }
3250
3251 jbd2_journal_clear_features(sbi->s_journal,
3252 JBD2_FEATURE_COMPAT_CHECKSUM, 0,
3253 JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_CSUM_V3 |
3254 JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_CSUM_V2);
3255 if (test_opt(sb, JOURNAL_ASYNC_COMMIT)) {
3256 ret = jbd2_journal_set_features(sbi->s_journal,
3257 compat, 0,
3258 JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_ASYNC_COMMIT |
3259 incompat);
3260 } else if (test_opt(sb, JOURNAL_CHECKSUM)) {
3261 ret = jbd2_journal_set_features(sbi->s_journal,
3262 compat, 0,
3263 incompat);
3264 jbd2_journal_clear_features(sbi->s_journal, 0, 0,
3265 JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_ASYNC_COMMIT);
3266 } else {
3267 jbd2_journal_clear_features(sbi->s_journal, 0, 0,
3268 JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_ASYNC_COMMIT);
3269 }
3270
3271 return ret;
3272}
3273
3274/*
3275 * Note: calculating the overhead so we can be compatible with
3276 * historical BSD practice is quite difficult in the face of
3277 * clusters/bigalloc. This is because multiple metadata blocks from
3278 * different block group can end up in the same allocation cluster.
3279 * Calculating the exact overhead in the face of clustered allocation
3280 * requires either O(all block bitmaps) in memory or O(number of block
3281 * groups**2) in time. We will still calculate the superblock for
3282 * older file systems --- and if we come across with a bigalloc file
3283 * system with zero in s_overhead_clusters the estimate will be close to
3284 * correct especially for very large cluster sizes --- but for newer
3285 * file systems, it's better to calculate this figure once at mkfs
3286 * time, and store it in the superblock. If the superblock value is
3287 * present (even for non-bigalloc file systems), we will use it.
3288 */
3289static int count_overhead(struct super_block *sb, ext4_group_t grp,
3290 char *buf)
3291{
3292 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
3293 struct ext4_group_desc *gdp;
3294 ext4_fsblk_t first_block, last_block, b;
3295 ext4_group_t i, ngroups = ext4_get_groups_count(sb);
3296 int s, j, count = 0;
3297
3298 if (!ext4_has_feature_bigalloc(sb))
3299 return (ext4_bg_has_super(sb, grp) + ext4_bg_num_gdb(sb, grp) +
3300 sbi->s_itb_per_group + 2);
3301
3302 first_block = le32_to_cpu(sbi->s_es->s_first_data_block) +
3303 (grp * EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb));
3304 last_block = first_block + EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb) - 1;
3305 for (i = 0; i < ngroups; i++) {
3306 gdp = ext4_get_group_desc(sb, i, NULL);
3307 b = ext4_block_bitmap(sb, gdp);
3308 if (b >= first_block && b <= last_block) {
3309 ext4_set_bit(EXT4_B2C(sbi, b - first_block), buf);
3310 count++;
3311 }
3312 b = ext4_inode_bitmap(sb, gdp);
3313 if (b >= first_block && b <= last_block) {
3314 ext4_set_bit(EXT4_B2C(sbi, b - first_block), buf);
3315 count++;
3316 }
3317 b = ext4_inode_table(sb, gdp);
3318 if (b >= first_block && b + sbi->s_itb_per_group <= last_block)
3319 for (j = 0; j < sbi->s_itb_per_group; j++, b++) {
3320 int c = EXT4_B2C(sbi, b - first_block);
3321 ext4_set_bit(c, buf);
3322 count++;
3323 }
3324 if (i != grp)
3325 continue;
3326 s = 0;
3327 if (ext4_bg_has_super(sb, grp)) {
3328 ext4_set_bit(s++, buf);
3329 count++;
3330 }
3331 j = ext4_bg_num_gdb(sb, grp);
3332 if (s + j > EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb)) {
3333 ext4_error(sb, "Invalid number of block group "
3334 "descriptor blocks: %d", j);
3335 j = EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb) - s;
3336 }
3337 count += j;
3338 for (; j > 0; j--)
3339 ext4_set_bit(EXT4_B2C(sbi, s++), buf);
3340 }
3341 if (!count)
3342 return 0;
3343 return EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb) -
3344 ext4_count_free(buf, EXT4_CLUSTERS_PER_GROUP(sb) / 8);
3345}
3346
3347/*
3348 * Compute the overhead and stash it in sbi->s_overhead
3349 */
3350int ext4_calculate_overhead(struct super_block *sb)
3351{
3352 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
3353 struct ext4_super_block *es = sbi->s_es;
3354 struct inode *j_inode;
3355 unsigned int j_blocks, j_inum = le32_to_cpu(es->s_journal_inum);
3356 ext4_group_t i, ngroups = ext4_get_groups_count(sb);
3357 ext4_fsblk_t overhead = 0;
3358 char *buf = (char *) get_zeroed_page(GFP_NOFS);
3359
3360 if (!buf)
3361 return -ENOMEM;
3362
3363 /*
3364 * Compute the overhead (FS structures). This is constant
3365 * for a given filesystem unless the number of block groups
3366 * changes so we cache the previous value until it does.
3367 */
3368
3369 /*
3370 * All of the blocks before first_data_block are overhead
3371 */
3372 overhead = EXT4_B2C(sbi, le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_data_block));
3373
3374 /*
3375 * Add the overhead found in each block group
3376 */
3377 for (i = 0; i < ngroups; i++) {
3378 int blks;
3379
3380 blks = count_overhead(sb, i, buf);
3381 overhead += blks;
3382 if (blks)
3383 memset(buf, 0, PAGE_SIZE);
3384 cond_resched();
3385 }
3386
3387 /*
3388 * Add the internal journal blocks whether the journal has been
3389 * loaded or not
3390 */
3391 if (sbi->s_journal && !sbi->journal_bdev)
3392 overhead += EXT4_NUM_B2C(sbi, sbi->s_journal->j_maxlen);
3393 else if (ext4_has_feature_journal(sb) && !sbi->s_journal) {
3394 j_inode = ext4_get_journal_inode(sb, j_inum);
3395 if (j_inode) {
3396 j_blocks = j_inode->i_size >> sb->s_blocksize_bits;
3397 overhead += EXT4_NUM_B2C(sbi, j_blocks);
3398 iput(j_inode);
3399 } else {
3400 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't get journal size");
3401 }
3402 }
3403 sbi->s_overhead = overhead;
3404 smp_wmb();
3405 free_page((unsigned long) buf);
3406 return 0;
3407}
3408
3409static void ext4_set_resv_clusters(struct super_block *sb)
3410{
3411 ext4_fsblk_t resv_clusters;
3412 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
3413
3414 /*
3415 * There's no need to reserve anything when we aren't using extents.
3416 * The space estimates are exact, there are no unwritten extents,
3417 * hole punching doesn't need new metadata... This is needed especially
3418 * to keep ext2/3 backward compatibility.
3419 */
3420 if (!ext4_has_feature_extents(sb))
3421 return;
3422 /*
3423 * By default we reserve 2% or 4096 clusters, whichever is smaller.
3424 * This should cover the situations where we can not afford to run
3425 * out of space like for example punch hole, or converting
3426 * unwritten extents in delalloc path. In most cases such
3427 * allocation would require 1, or 2 blocks, higher numbers are
3428 * very rare.
3429 */
3430 resv_clusters = (ext4_blocks_count(sbi->s_es) >>
3431 sbi->s_cluster_bits);
3432
3433 do_div(resv_clusters, 50);
3434 resv_clusters = min_t(ext4_fsblk_t, resv_clusters, 4096);
3435
3436 atomic64_set(&sbi->s_resv_clusters, resv_clusters);
3437}
3438
3439static int ext4_fill_super(struct super_block *sb, void *data, int silent)
3440{
3441 struct dax_device *dax_dev = fs_dax_get_by_bdev(sb->s_bdev);
3442 char *orig_data = kstrdup(data, GFP_KERNEL);
3443 struct buffer_head *bh;
3444 struct ext4_super_block *es = NULL;
3445 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = kzalloc(sizeof(*sbi), GFP_KERNEL);
3446 ext4_fsblk_t block;
3447 ext4_fsblk_t sb_block = get_sb_block(&data);
3448 ext4_fsblk_t logical_sb_block;
3449 unsigned long offset = 0;
3450 unsigned long journal_devnum = 0;
3451 unsigned long def_mount_opts;
3452 struct inode *root;
3453 const char *descr;
3454 int ret = -ENOMEM;
3455 int blocksize, clustersize;
3456 unsigned int db_count;
3457 unsigned int i;
3458 int needs_recovery, has_huge_files, has_bigalloc;
3459 __u64 blocks_count;
3460 int err = 0;
3461 unsigned int journal_ioprio = DEFAULT_JOURNAL_IOPRIO;
3462 ext4_group_t first_not_zeroed;
3463
3464 if ((data && !orig_data) || !sbi)
3465 goto out_free_base;
3466
3467 sbi->s_daxdev = dax_dev;
3468 sbi->s_blockgroup_lock =
3469 kzalloc(sizeof(struct blockgroup_lock), GFP_KERNEL);
3470 if (!sbi->s_blockgroup_lock)
3471 goto out_free_base;
3472
3473 sb->s_fs_info = sbi;
3474 sbi->s_sb = sb;
3475 sbi->s_inode_readahead_blks = EXT4_DEF_INODE_READAHEAD_BLKS;
3476 sbi->s_sb_block = sb_block;
3477 if (sb->s_bdev->bd_part)
3478 sbi->s_sectors_written_start =
3479 part_stat_read(sb->s_bdev->bd_part, sectors[1]);
3480
3481 /* Cleanup superblock name */
3482 strreplace(sb->s_id, '/', '!');
3483
3484 /* -EINVAL is default */
3485 ret = -EINVAL;
3486 blocksize = sb_min_blocksize(sb, EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE);
3487 if (!blocksize) {
3488 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "unable to set blocksize");
3489 goto out_fail;
3490 }
3491
3492 /*
3493 * The ext4 superblock will not be buffer aligned for other than 1kB
3494 * block sizes. We need to calculate the offset from buffer start.
3495 */
3496 if (blocksize != EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3497 logical_sb_block = sb_block * EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE;
3498 offset = do_div(logical_sb_block, blocksize);
3499 } else {
3500 logical_sb_block = sb_block;
3501 }
3502
3503 if (!(bh = sb_bread_unmovable(sb, logical_sb_block))) {
3504 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "unable to read superblock");
3505 goto out_fail;
3506 }
3507 /*
3508 * Note: s_es must be initialized as soon as possible because
3509 * some ext4 macro-instructions depend on its value
3510 */
3511 es = (struct ext4_super_block *) (bh->b_data + offset);
3512 sbi->s_es = es;
3513 sb->s_magic = le16_to_cpu(es->s_magic);
3514 if (sb->s_magic != EXT4_SUPER_MAGIC)
3515 goto cantfind_ext4;
3516 sbi->s_kbytes_written = le64_to_cpu(es->s_kbytes_written);
3517
3518 /* Warn if metadata_csum and gdt_csum are both set. */
3519 if (ext4_has_feature_metadata_csum(sb) &&
3520 ext4_has_feature_gdt_csum(sb))
3521 ext4_warning(sb, "metadata_csum and uninit_bg are "
3522 "redundant flags; please run fsck.");
3523
3524 /* Check for a known checksum algorithm */
3525 if (!ext4_verify_csum_type(sb, es)) {
3526 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "VFS: Found ext4 filesystem with "
3527 "unknown checksum algorithm.");
3528 silent = 1;
3529 goto cantfind_ext4;
3530 }
3531
3532 /* Load the checksum driver */
3533 sbi->s_chksum_driver = crypto_alloc_shash("crc32c", 0, 0);
3534 if (IS_ERR(sbi->s_chksum_driver)) {
3535 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Cannot load crc32c driver.");
3536 ret = PTR_ERR(sbi->s_chksum_driver);
3537 sbi->s_chksum_driver = NULL;
3538 goto failed_mount;
3539 }
3540
3541 /* Check superblock checksum */
3542 if (!ext4_superblock_csum_verify(sb, es)) {
3543 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "VFS: Found ext4 filesystem with "
3544 "invalid superblock checksum. Run e2fsck?");
3545 silent = 1;
3546 ret = -EFSBADCRC;
3547 goto cantfind_ext4;
3548 }
3549
3550 /* Precompute checksum seed for all metadata */
3551 if (ext4_has_feature_csum_seed(sb))
3552 sbi->s_csum_seed = le32_to_cpu(es->s_checksum_seed);
3553 else if (ext4_has_metadata_csum(sb) || ext4_has_feature_ea_inode(sb))
3554 sbi->s_csum_seed = ext4_chksum(sbi, ~0, es->s_uuid,
3555 sizeof(es->s_uuid));
3556
3557 /* Set defaults before we parse the mount options */
3558 def_mount_opts = le32_to_cpu(es->s_default_mount_opts);
3559 set_opt(sb, INIT_INODE_TABLE);
3560 if (def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_DEBUG)
3561 set_opt(sb, DEBUG);
3562 if (def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_BSDGROUPS)
3563 set_opt(sb, GRPID);
3564 if (def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_UID16)
3565 set_opt(sb, NO_UID32);
3566 /* xattr user namespace & acls are now defaulted on */
3567 set_opt(sb, XATTR_USER);
3568#ifdef CONFIG_EXT4_FS_POSIX_ACL
3569 set_opt(sb, POSIX_ACL);
3570#endif
3571 /* don't forget to enable journal_csum when metadata_csum is enabled. */
3572 if (ext4_has_metadata_csum(sb))
3573 set_opt(sb, JOURNAL_CHECKSUM);
3574
3575 if ((def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_JMODE) == EXT4_DEFM_JMODE_DATA)
3576 set_opt(sb, JOURNAL_DATA);
3577 else if ((def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_JMODE) == EXT4_DEFM_JMODE_ORDERED)
3578 set_opt(sb, ORDERED_DATA);
3579 else if ((def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_JMODE) == EXT4_DEFM_JMODE_WBACK)
3580 set_opt(sb, WRITEBACK_DATA);
3581
3582 if (le16_to_cpu(sbi->s_es->s_errors) == EXT4_ERRORS_PANIC)
3583 set_opt(sb, ERRORS_PANIC);
3584 else if (le16_to_cpu(sbi->s_es->s_errors) == EXT4_ERRORS_CONTINUE)
3585 set_opt(sb, ERRORS_CONT);
3586 else
3587 set_opt(sb, ERRORS_RO);
3588 /* block_validity enabled by default; disable with noblock_validity */
3589 set_opt(sb, BLOCK_VALIDITY);
3590 if (def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_DISCARD)
3591 set_opt(sb, DISCARD);
3592
3593 sbi->s_resuid = make_kuid(&init_user_ns, le16_to_cpu(es->s_def_resuid));
3594 sbi->s_resgid = make_kgid(&init_user_ns, le16_to_cpu(es->s_def_resgid));
3595 sbi->s_commit_interval = JBD2_DEFAULT_MAX_COMMIT_AGE * HZ;
3596 sbi->s_min_batch_time = EXT4_DEF_MIN_BATCH_TIME;
3597 sbi->s_max_batch_time = EXT4_DEF_MAX_BATCH_TIME;
3598
3599 if ((def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_NOBARRIER) == 0)
3600 set_opt(sb, BARRIER);
3601
3602 /*
3603 * enable delayed allocation by default
3604 * Use -o nodelalloc to turn it off
3605 */
3606 if (!IS_EXT3_SB(sb) && !IS_EXT2_SB(sb) &&
3607 ((def_mount_opts & EXT4_DEFM_NODELALLOC) == 0))
3608 set_opt(sb, DELALLOC);
3609
3610 /*
3611 * set default s_li_wait_mult for lazyinit, for the case there is
3612 * no mount option specified.
3613 */
3614 sbi->s_li_wait_mult = EXT4_DEF_LI_WAIT_MULT;
3615
3616 if (sbi->s_es->s_mount_opts[0]) {
3617 char *s_mount_opts = kstrndup(sbi->s_es->s_mount_opts,
3618 sizeof(sbi->s_es->s_mount_opts),
3619 GFP_KERNEL);
3620 if (!s_mount_opts)
3621 goto failed_mount;
3622 if (!parse_options(s_mount_opts, sb, &journal_devnum,
3623 &journal_ioprio, 0)) {
3624 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING,
3625 "failed to parse options in superblock: %s",
3626 s_mount_opts);
3627 }
3628 kfree(s_mount_opts);
3629 }
3630 sbi->s_def_mount_opt = sbi->s_mount_opt;
3631 if (!parse_options((char *) data, sb, &journal_devnum,
3632 &journal_ioprio, 0))
3633 goto failed_mount;
3634
3635 if (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS) == EXT4_MOUNT_JOURNAL_DATA) {
3636 printk_once(KERN_WARNING "EXT4-fs: Warning: mounting "
3637 "with data=journal disables delayed "
3638 "allocation and O_DIRECT support!\n");
3639 if (test_opt2(sb, EXPLICIT_DELALLOC)) {
3640 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
3641 "both data=journal and delalloc");
3642 goto failed_mount;
3643 }
3644 if (test_opt(sb, DIOREAD_NOLOCK)) {
3645 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
3646 "both data=journal and dioread_nolock");
3647 goto failed_mount;
3648 }
3649 if (test_opt(sb, DAX)) {
3650 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
3651 "both data=journal and dax");
3652 goto failed_mount;
3653 }
3654 if (ext4_has_feature_encrypt(sb)) {
3655 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING,
3656 "encrypted files will use data=ordered "
3657 "instead of data journaling mode");
3658 }
3659 if (test_opt(sb, DELALLOC))
3660 clear_opt(sb, DELALLOC);
3661 } else {
3662 sb->s_iflags |= SB_I_CGROUPWB;
3663 }
3664
3665 sb->s_flags = (sb->s_flags & ~MS_POSIXACL) |
3666 (test_opt(sb, POSIX_ACL) ? MS_POSIXACL : 0);
3667
3668 if (le32_to_cpu(es->s_rev_level) == EXT4_GOOD_OLD_REV &&
3669 (ext4_has_compat_features(sb) ||
3670 ext4_has_ro_compat_features(sb) ||
3671 ext4_has_incompat_features(sb)))
3672 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING,
3673 "feature flags set on rev 0 fs, "
3674 "running e2fsck is recommended");
3675
3676 if (es->s_creator_os == cpu_to_le32(EXT4_OS_HURD)) {
3677 set_opt2(sb, HURD_COMPAT);
3678 if (ext4_has_feature_64bit(sb)) {
3679 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3680 "The Hurd can't support 64-bit file systems");
3681 goto failed_mount;
3682 }
3683
3684 /*
3685 * ea_inode feature uses l_i_version field which is not
3686 * available in HURD_COMPAT mode.
3687 */
3688 if (ext4_has_feature_ea_inode(sb)) {
3689 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3690 "ea_inode feature is not supported for Hurd");
3691 goto failed_mount;
3692 }
3693 }
3694
3695 if (IS_EXT2_SB(sb)) {
3696 if (ext2_feature_set_ok(sb))
3697 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "mounting ext2 file system "
3698 "using the ext4 subsystem");
3699 else {
3700 /*
3701 * If we're probing be silent, if this looks like
3702 * it's actually an ext[34] filesystem.
3703 */
3704 if (silent && ext4_feature_set_ok(sb, sb_rdonly(sb)))
3705 goto failed_mount;
3706 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "couldn't mount as ext2 due "
3707 "to feature incompatibilities");
3708 goto failed_mount;
3709 }
3710 }
3711
3712 if (IS_EXT3_SB(sb)) {
3713 if (ext3_feature_set_ok(sb))
3714 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "mounting ext3 file system "
3715 "using the ext4 subsystem");
3716 else {
3717 /*
3718 * If we're probing be silent, if this looks like
3719 * it's actually an ext4 filesystem.
3720 */
3721 if (silent && ext4_feature_set_ok(sb, sb_rdonly(sb)))
3722 goto failed_mount;
3723 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "couldn't mount as ext3 due "
3724 "to feature incompatibilities");
3725 goto failed_mount;
3726 }
3727 }
3728
3729 /*
3730 * Check feature flags regardless of the revision level, since we
3731 * previously didn't change the revision level when setting the flags,
3732 * so there is a chance incompat flags are set on a rev 0 filesystem.
3733 */
3734 if (!ext4_feature_set_ok(sb, (sb_rdonly(sb))))
3735 goto failed_mount;
3736
3737 blocksize = BLOCK_SIZE << le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_block_size);
3738 if (blocksize < EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE ||
3739 blocksize > EXT4_MAX_BLOCK_SIZE) {
3740 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3741 "Unsupported filesystem blocksize %d (%d log_block_size)",
3742 blocksize, le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_block_size));
3743 goto failed_mount;
3744 }
3745 if (le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_block_size) >
3746 (EXT4_MAX_BLOCK_LOG_SIZE - EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_LOG_SIZE)) {
3747 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3748 "Invalid log block size: %u",
3749 le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_block_size));
3750 goto failed_mount;
3751 }
3752 if (le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_cluster_size) >
3753 (EXT4_MAX_CLUSTER_LOG_SIZE - EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_LOG_SIZE)) {
3754 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3755 "Invalid log cluster size: %u",
3756 le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_cluster_size));
3757 goto failed_mount;
3758 }
3759
3760 if (le16_to_cpu(sbi->s_es->s_reserved_gdt_blocks) > (blocksize / 4)) {
3761 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3762 "Number of reserved GDT blocks insanely large: %d",
3763 le16_to_cpu(sbi->s_es->s_reserved_gdt_blocks));
3764 goto failed_mount;
3765 }
3766
3767 if (sbi->s_mount_opt & EXT4_MOUNT_DAX) {
3768 if (ext4_has_feature_inline_data(sb)) {
3769 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Cannot use DAX on a filesystem"
3770 " that may contain inline data");
3771 goto failed_mount;
3772 }
3773 if (!bdev_dax_supported(sb->s_bdev, blocksize))
3774 goto failed_mount;
3775 }
3776
3777 if (ext4_has_feature_encrypt(sb) && es->s_encryption_level) {
3778 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Unsupported encryption level %d",
3779 es->s_encryption_level);
3780 goto failed_mount;
3781 }
3782
3783 if (sb->s_blocksize != blocksize) {
3784 /* Validate the filesystem blocksize */
3785 if (!sb_set_blocksize(sb, blocksize)) {
3786 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "bad block size %d",
3787 blocksize);
3788 goto failed_mount;
3789 }
3790
3791 brelse(bh);
3792 logical_sb_block = sb_block * EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE;
3793 offset = do_div(logical_sb_block, blocksize);
3794 bh = sb_bread_unmovable(sb, logical_sb_block);
3795 if (!bh) {
3796 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3797 "Can't read superblock on 2nd try");
3798 goto failed_mount;
3799 }
3800 es = (struct ext4_super_block *)(bh->b_data + offset);
3801 sbi->s_es = es;
3802 if (es->s_magic != cpu_to_le16(EXT4_SUPER_MAGIC)) {
3803 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3804 "Magic mismatch, very weird!");
3805 goto failed_mount;
3806 }
3807 }
3808
3809 has_huge_files = ext4_has_feature_huge_file(sb);
3810 sbi->s_bitmap_maxbytes = ext4_max_bitmap_size(sb->s_blocksize_bits,
3811 has_huge_files);
3812 sb->s_maxbytes = ext4_max_size(sb->s_blocksize_bits, has_huge_files);
3813
3814 if (le32_to_cpu(es->s_rev_level) == EXT4_GOOD_OLD_REV) {
3815 sbi->s_inode_size = EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE;
3816 sbi->s_first_ino = EXT4_GOOD_OLD_FIRST_INO;
3817 } else {
3818 sbi->s_inode_size = le16_to_cpu(es->s_inode_size);
3819 sbi->s_first_ino = le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_ino);
3820 if (sbi->s_first_ino < EXT4_GOOD_OLD_FIRST_INO) {
3821 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "invalid first ino: %u",
3822 sbi->s_first_ino);
3823 goto failed_mount;
3824 }
3825 if ((sbi->s_inode_size < EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE) ||
3826 (!is_power_of_2(sbi->s_inode_size)) ||
3827 (sbi->s_inode_size > blocksize)) {
3828 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3829 "unsupported inode size: %d",
3830 sbi->s_inode_size);
3831 goto failed_mount;
3832 }
3833 if (sbi->s_inode_size > EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE)
3834 sb->s_time_gran = 1 << (EXT4_EPOCH_BITS - 2);
3835 }
3836
3837 sbi->s_desc_size = le16_to_cpu(es->s_desc_size);
3838 if (ext4_has_feature_64bit(sb)) {
3839 if (sbi->s_desc_size < EXT4_MIN_DESC_SIZE_64BIT ||
3840 sbi->s_desc_size > EXT4_MAX_DESC_SIZE ||
3841 !is_power_of_2(sbi->s_desc_size)) {
3842 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3843 "unsupported descriptor size %lu",
3844 sbi->s_desc_size);
3845 goto failed_mount;
3846 }
3847 } else
3848 sbi->s_desc_size = EXT4_MIN_DESC_SIZE;
3849
3850 sbi->s_blocks_per_group = le32_to_cpu(es->s_blocks_per_group);
3851 sbi->s_inodes_per_group = le32_to_cpu(es->s_inodes_per_group);
3852
3853 sbi->s_inodes_per_block = blocksize / EXT4_INODE_SIZE(sb);
3854 if (sbi->s_inodes_per_block == 0)
3855 goto cantfind_ext4;
3856 if (sbi->s_inodes_per_group < sbi->s_inodes_per_block ||
3857 sbi->s_inodes_per_group > blocksize * 8) {
3858 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "invalid inodes per group: %lu\n",
3859 sbi->s_blocks_per_group);
3860 goto failed_mount;
3861 }
3862 sbi->s_itb_per_group = sbi->s_inodes_per_group /
3863 sbi->s_inodes_per_block;
3864 sbi->s_desc_per_block = blocksize / EXT4_DESC_SIZE(sb);
3865 sbi->s_sbh = bh;
3866 sbi->s_mount_state = le16_to_cpu(es->s_state);
3867 sbi->s_addr_per_block_bits = ilog2(EXT4_ADDR_PER_BLOCK(sb));
3868 sbi->s_desc_per_block_bits = ilog2(EXT4_DESC_PER_BLOCK(sb));
3869
3870 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
3871 sbi->s_hash_seed[i] = le32_to_cpu(es->s_hash_seed[i]);
3872 sbi->s_def_hash_version = es->s_def_hash_version;
3873 if (ext4_has_feature_dir_index(sb)) {
3874 i = le32_to_cpu(es->s_flags);
3875 if (i & EXT2_FLAGS_UNSIGNED_HASH)
3876 sbi->s_hash_unsigned = 3;
3877 else if ((i & EXT2_FLAGS_SIGNED_HASH) == 0) {
3878#ifdef __CHAR_UNSIGNED__
3879 if (!sb_rdonly(sb))
3880 es->s_flags |=
3881 cpu_to_le32(EXT2_FLAGS_UNSIGNED_HASH);
3882 sbi->s_hash_unsigned = 3;
3883#else
3884 if (!sb_rdonly(sb))
3885 es->s_flags |=
3886 cpu_to_le32(EXT2_FLAGS_SIGNED_HASH);
3887#endif
3888 }
3889 }
3890
3891 /* Handle clustersize */
3892 clustersize = BLOCK_SIZE << le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_cluster_size);
3893 has_bigalloc = ext4_has_feature_bigalloc(sb);
3894 if (has_bigalloc) {
3895 if (clustersize < blocksize) {
3896 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3897 "cluster size (%d) smaller than "
3898 "block size (%d)", clustersize, blocksize);
3899 goto failed_mount;
3900 }
3901 sbi->s_cluster_bits = le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_cluster_size) -
3902 le32_to_cpu(es->s_log_block_size);
3903 sbi->s_clusters_per_group =
3904 le32_to_cpu(es->s_clusters_per_group);
3905 if (sbi->s_clusters_per_group > blocksize * 8) {
3906 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3907 "#clusters per group too big: %lu",
3908 sbi->s_clusters_per_group);
3909 goto failed_mount;
3910 }
3911 if (sbi->s_blocks_per_group !=
3912 (sbi->s_clusters_per_group * (clustersize / blocksize))) {
3913 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "blocks per group (%lu) and "
3914 "clusters per group (%lu) inconsistent",
3915 sbi->s_blocks_per_group,
3916 sbi->s_clusters_per_group);
3917 goto failed_mount;
3918 }
3919 } else {
3920 if (clustersize != blocksize) {
3921 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3922 "fragment/cluster size (%d) != "
3923 "block size (%d)", clustersize, blocksize);
3924 goto failed_mount;
3925 }
3926 if (sbi->s_blocks_per_group > blocksize * 8) {
3927 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
3928 "#blocks per group too big: %lu",
3929 sbi->s_blocks_per_group);
3930 goto failed_mount;
3931 }
3932 sbi->s_clusters_per_group = sbi->s_blocks_per_group;
3933 sbi->s_cluster_bits = 0;
3934 }
3935 sbi->s_cluster_ratio = clustersize / blocksize;
3936
3937 /* Do we have standard group size of clustersize * 8 blocks ? */
3938 if (sbi->s_blocks_per_group == clustersize << 3)
3939 set_opt2(sb, STD_GROUP_SIZE);
3940
3941 /*
3942 * Test whether we have more sectors than will fit in sector_t,
3943 * and whether the max offset is addressable by the page cache.
3944 */
3945 err = generic_check_addressable(sb->s_blocksize_bits,
3946 ext4_blocks_count(es));
3947 if (err) {
3948 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "filesystem"
3949 " too large to mount safely on this system");
3950 if (sizeof(sector_t) < 8)
3951 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "CONFIG_LBDAF not enabled");
3952 goto failed_mount;
3953 }
3954
3955 if (EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb) == 0)
3956 goto cantfind_ext4;
3957
3958 /* check blocks count against device size */
3959 blocks_count = sb->s_bdev->bd_inode->i_size >> sb->s_blocksize_bits;
3960 if (blocks_count && ext4_blocks_count(es) > blocks_count) {
3961 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "bad geometry: block count %llu "
3962 "exceeds size of device (%llu blocks)",
3963 ext4_blocks_count(es), blocks_count);
3964 goto failed_mount;
3965 }
3966
3967 /*
3968 * It makes no sense for the first data block to be beyond the end
3969 * of the filesystem.
3970 */
3971 if (le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_data_block) >= ext4_blocks_count(es)) {
3972 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "bad geometry: first data "
3973 "block %u is beyond end of filesystem (%llu)",
3974 le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_data_block),
3975 ext4_blocks_count(es));
3976 goto failed_mount;
3977 }
3978 if ((es->s_first_data_block == 0) && (es->s_log_block_size == 0) &&
3979 (sbi->s_cluster_ratio == 1)) {
3980 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "bad geometry: first data "
3981 "block is 0 with a 1k block and cluster size");
3982 goto failed_mount;
3983 }
3984
3985 blocks_count = (ext4_blocks_count(es) -
3986 le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_data_block) +
3987 EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb) - 1);
3988 do_div(blocks_count, EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb));
3989 if (blocks_count > ((uint64_t)1<<32) - EXT4_DESC_PER_BLOCK(sb)) {
3990 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "groups count too large: %u "
3991 "(block count %llu, first data block %u, "
3992 "blocks per group %lu)", sbi->s_groups_count,
3993 ext4_blocks_count(es),
3994 le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_data_block),
3995 EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb));
3996 goto failed_mount;
3997 }
3998 sbi->s_groups_count = blocks_count;
3999 sbi->s_blockfile_groups = min_t(ext4_group_t, sbi->s_groups_count,
4000 (EXT4_MAX_BLOCK_FILE_PHYS / EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(sb)));
4001 db_count = (sbi->s_groups_count + EXT4_DESC_PER_BLOCK(sb) - 1) /
4002 EXT4_DESC_PER_BLOCK(sb);
4003 if (ext4_has_feature_meta_bg(sb)) {
4004 if (le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_meta_bg) > db_count) {
4005 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING,
4006 "first meta block group too large: %u "
4007 "(group descriptor block count %u)",
4008 le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_meta_bg), db_count);
4009 goto failed_mount;
4010 }
4011 }
4012 sbi->s_group_desc = kvmalloc(db_count *
4013 sizeof(struct buffer_head *),
4014 GFP_KERNEL);
4015 if (sbi->s_group_desc == NULL) {
4016 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "not enough memory");
4017 ret = -ENOMEM;
4018 goto failed_mount;
4019 }
4020 if (((u64)sbi->s_groups_count * sbi->s_inodes_per_group) !=
4021 le32_to_cpu(es->s_inodes_count)) {
4022 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "inodes count not valid: %u vs %llu",
4023 le32_to_cpu(es->s_inodes_count),
4024 ((u64)sbi->s_groups_count * sbi->s_inodes_per_group));
4025 ret = -EINVAL;
4026 goto failed_mount;
4027 }
4028
4029 bgl_lock_init(sbi->s_blockgroup_lock);
4030
4031 /* Pre-read the descriptors into the buffer cache */
4032 for (i = 0; i < db_count; i++) {
4033 block = descriptor_loc(sb, logical_sb_block, i);
4034 sb_breadahead(sb, block);
4035 }
4036
4037 for (i = 0; i < db_count; i++) {
4038 block = descriptor_loc(sb, logical_sb_block, i);
4039 sbi->s_group_desc[i] = sb_bread_unmovable(sb, block);
4040 if (!sbi->s_group_desc[i]) {
4041 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
4042 "can't read group descriptor %d", i);
4043 db_count = i;
4044 goto failed_mount2;
4045 }
4046 }
4047 if (!ext4_check_descriptors(sb, logical_sb_block, &first_not_zeroed)) {
4048 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "group descriptors corrupted!");
4049 ret = -EFSCORRUPTED;
4050 goto failed_mount2;
4051 }
4052
4053 sbi->s_gdb_count = db_count;
4054 get_random_bytes(&sbi->s_next_generation, sizeof(u32));
4055 spin_lock_init(&sbi->s_next_gen_lock);
4056
4057 setup_timer(&sbi->s_err_report, print_daily_error_info,
4058 (unsigned long) sb);
4059
4060 /* Register extent status tree shrinker */
4061 if (ext4_es_register_shrinker(sbi))
4062 goto failed_mount3;
4063
4064 sbi->s_stripe = ext4_get_stripe_size(sbi);
4065 sbi->s_extent_max_zeroout_kb = 32;
4066
4067 /*
4068 * set up enough so that it can read an inode
4069 */
4070 sb->s_op = &ext4_sops;
4071 sb->s_export_op = &ext4_export_ops;
4072 sb->s_xattr = ext4_xattr_handlers;
4073 sb->s_cop = &ext4_cryptops;
4074#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
4075 sb->dq_op = &ext4_quota_operations;
4076 if (ext4_has_feature_quota(sb))
4077 sb->s_qcop = &dquot_quotactl_sysfile_ops;
4078 else
4079 sb->s_qcop = &ext4_qctl_operations;
4080 sb->s_quota_types = QTYPE_MASK_USR | QTYPE_MASK_GRP | QTYPE_MASK_PRJ;
4081#endif
4082 memcpy(&sb->s_uuid, es->s_uuid, sizeof(es->s_uuid));
4083
4084 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&sbi->s_orphan); /* unlinked but open files */
4085 mutex_init(&sbi->s_orphan_lock);
4086
4087 sb->s_root = NULL;
4088
4089 needs_recovery = (es->s_last_orphan != 0 ||
4090 ext4_has_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb));
4091
4092 if (ext4_has_feature_mmp(sb) && !sb_rdonly(sb))
4093 if (ext4_multi_mount_protect(sb, le64_to_cpu(es->s_mmp_block)))
4094 goto failed_mount3a;
4095
4096 /*
4097 * The first inode we look at is the journal inode. Don't try
4098 * root first: it may be modified in the journal!
4099 */
4100 if (!test_opt(sb, NOLOAD) && ext4_has_feature_journal(sb)) {
4101 err = ext4_load_journal(sb, es, journal_devnum);
4102 if (err)
4103 goto failed_mount3a;
4104 } else if (test_opt(sb, NOLOAD) && !sb_rdonly(sb) &&
4105 ext4_has_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb)) {
4106 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "required journal recovery "
4107 "suppressed and not mounted read-only");
4108 goto failed_mount_wq;
4109 } else {
4110 /* Nojournal mode, all journal mount options are illegal */
4111 if (test_opt2(sb, EXPLICIT_JOURNAL_CHECKSUM)) {
4112 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
4113 "journal_checksum, fs mounted w/o journal");
4114 goto failed_mount_wq;
4115 }
4116 if (test_opt(sb, JOURNAL_ASYNC_COMMIT)) {
4117 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
4118 "journal_async_commit, fs mounted w/o journal");
4119 goto failed_mount_wq;
4120 }
4121 if (sbi->s_commit_interval != JBD2_DEFAULT_MAX_COMMIT_AGE*HZ) {
4122 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
4123 "commit=%lu, fs mounted w/o journal",
4124 sbi->s_commit_interval / HZ);
4125 goto failed_mount_wq;
4126 }
4127 if (EXT4_MOUNT_DATA_FLAGS &
4128 (sbi->s_mount_opt ^ sbi->s_def_mount_opt)) {
4129 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
4130 "data=, fs mounted w/o journal");
4131 goto failed_mount_wq;
4132 }
4133 sbi->s_def_mount_opt &= EXT4_MOUNT_JOURNAL_CHECKSUM;
4134 clear_opt(sb, JOURNAL_CHECKSUM);
4135 clear_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS);
4136 sbi->s_journal = NULL;
4137 needs_recovery = 0;
4138 goto no_journal;
4139 }
4140
4141 if (ext4_has_feature_64bit(sb) &&
4142 !jbd2_journal_set_features(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal, 0, 0,
4143 JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_64BIT)) {
4144 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Failed to set 64-bit journal feature");
4145 goto failed_mount_wq;
4146 }
4147
4148 if (!set_journal_csum_feature_set(sb)) {
4149 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Failed to set journal checksum "
4150 "feature set");
4151 goto failed_mount_wq;
4152 }
4153
4154 /* We have now updated the journal if required, so we can
4155 * validate the data journaling mode. */
4156 switch (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS)) {
4157 case 0:
4158 /* No mode set, assume a default based on the journal
4159 * capabilities: ORDERED_DATA if the journal can
4160 * cope, else JOURNAL_DATA
4161 */
4162 if (jbd2_journal_check_available_features
4163 (sbi->s_journal, 0, 0, JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_REVOKE))
4164 set_opt(sb, ORDERED_DATA);
4165 else
4166 set_opt(sb, JOURNAL_DATA);
4167 break;
4168
4169 case EXT4_MOUNT_ORDERED_DATA:
4170 case EXT4_MOUNT_WRITEBACK_DATA:
4171 if (!jbd2_journal_check_available_features
4172 (sbi->s_journal, 0, 0, JBD2_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_REVOKE)) {
4173 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Journal does not support "
4174 "requested data journaling mode");
4175 goto failed_mount_wq;
4176 }
4177 default:
4178 break;
4179 }
4180
4181 if (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS) == EXT4_MOUNT_ORDERED_DATA &&
4182 test_opt(sb, JOURNAL_ASYNC_COMMIT)) {
4183 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
4184 "journal_async_commit in data=ordered mode");
4185 goto failed_mount_wq;
4186 }
4187
4188 set_task_ioprio(sbi->s_journal->j_task, journal_ioprio);
4189
4190 sbi->s_journal->j_commit_callback = ext4_journal_commit_callback;
4191
4192no_journal:
4193 if (!test_opt(sb, NO_MBCACHE)) {
4194 sbi->s_ea_block_cache = ext4_xattr_create_cache();
4195 if (!sbi->s_ea_block_cache) {
4196 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
4197 "Failed to create ea_block_cache");
4198 goto failed_mount_wq;
4199 }
4200
4201 if (ext4_has_feature_ea_inode(sb)) {
4202 sbi->s_ea_inode_cache = ext4_xattr_create_cache();
4203 if (!sbi->s_ea_inode_cache) {
4204 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
4205 "Failed to create ea_inode_cache");
4206 goto failed_mount_wq;
4207 }
4208 }
4209 }
4210
4211 if ((DUMMY_ENCRYPTION_ENABLED(sbi) || ext4_has_feature_encrypt(sb)) &&
4212 (blocksize != PAGE_SIZE)) {
4213 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
4214 "Unsupported blocksize for fs encryption");
4215 goto failed_mount_wq;
4216 }
4217
4218 if (DUMMY_ENCRYPTION_ENABLED(sbi) && !sb_rdonly(sb) &&
4219 !ext4_has_feature_encrypt(sb)) {
4220 ext4_set_feature_encrypt(sb);
4221 ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
4222 }
4223
4224 /*
4225 * Get the # of file system overhead blocks from the
4226 * superblock if present.
4227 */
4228 if (es->s_overhead_clusters)
4229 sbi->s_overhead = le32_to_cpu(es->s_overhead_clusters);
4230 else {
4231 err = ext4_calculate_overhead(sb);
4232 if (err)
4233 goto failed_mount_wq;
4234 }
4235
4236 /*
4237 * The maximum number of concurrent works can be high and
4238 * concurrency isn't really necessary. Limit it to 1.
4239 */
4240 EXT4_SB(sb)->rsv_conversion_wq =
4241 alloc_workqueue("ext4-rsv-conversion", WQ_MEM_RECLAIM | WQ_UNBOUND, 1);
4242 if (!EXT4_SB(sb)->rsv_conversion_wq) {
4243 printk(KERN_ERR "EXT4-fs: failed to create workqueue\n");
4244 ret = -ENOMEM;
4245 goto failed_mount4;
4246 }
4247
4248 /*
4249 * The jbd2_journal_load will have done any necessary log recovery,
4250 * so we can safely mount the rest of the filesystem now.
4251 */
4252
4253 root = ext4_iget(sb, EXT4_ROOT_INO);
4254 if (IS_ERR(root)) {
4255 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "get root inode failed");
4256 ret = PTR_ERR(root);
4257 root = NULL;
4258 goto failed_mount4;
4259 }
4260 if (!S_ISDIR(root->i_mode) || !root->i_blocks || !root->i_size) {
4261 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "corrupt root inode, run e2fsck");
4262 iput(root);
4263 goto failed_mount4;
4264 }
4265 sb->s_root = d_make_root(root);
4266 if (!sb->s_root) {
4267 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "get root dentry failed");
4268 ret = -ENOMEM;
4269 goto failed_mount4;
4270 }
4271
4272 if (ext4_setup_super(sb, es, sb_rdonly(sb)))
4273 sb->s_flags |= MS_RDONLY;
4274
4275 /* determine the minimum size of new large inodes, if present */
4276 if (sbi->s_inode_size > EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE &&
4277 sbi->s_want_extra_isize == 0) {
4278 sbi->s_want_extra_isize = sizeof(struct ext4_inode) -
4279 EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE;
4280 if (ext4_has_feature_extra_isize(sb)) {
4281 if (sbi->s_want_extra_isize <
4282 le16_to_cpu(es->s_want_extra_isize))
4283 sbi->s_want_extra_isize =
4284 le16_to_cpu(es->s_want_extra_isize);
4285 if (sbi->s_want_extra_isize <
4286 le16_to_cpu(es->s_min_extra_isize))
4287 sbi->s_want_extra_isize =
4288 le16_to_cpu(es->s_min_extra_isize);
4289 }
4290 }
4291 /* Check if enough inode space is available */
4292 if (EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE + sbi->s_want_extra_isize >
4293 sbi->s_inode_size) {
4294 sbi->s_want_extra_isize = sizeof(struct ext4_inode) -
4295 EXT4_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE;
4296 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "required extra inode space not"
4297 "available");
4298 }
4299
4300 ext4_set_resv_clusters(sb);
4301
4302 err = ext4_setup_system_zone(sb);
4303 if (err) {
4304 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "failed to initialize system "
4305 "zone (%d)", err);
4306 goto failed_mount4a;
4307 }
4308
4309 ext4_ext_init(sb);
4310 err = ext4_mb_init(sb);
4311 if (err) {
4312 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "failed to initialize mballoc (%d)",
4313 err);
4314 goto failed_mount5;
4315 }
4316
4317 block = ext4_count_free_clusters(sb);
4318 ext4_free_blocks_count_set(sbi->s_es,
4319 EXT4_C2B(sbi, block));
4320 err = percpu_counter_init(&sbi->s_freeclusters_counter, block,
4321 GFP_KERNEL);
4322 if (!err) {
4323 unsigned long freei = ext4_count_free_inodes(sb);
4324 sbi->s_es->s_free_inodes_count = cpu_to_le32(freei);
4325 err = percpu_counter_init(&sbi->s_freeinodes_counter, freei,
4326 GFP_KERNEL);
4327 }
4328 if (!err)
4329 err = percpu_counter_init(&sbi->s_dirs_counter,
4330 ext4_count_dirs(sb), GFP_KERNEL);
4331 if (!err)
4332 err = percpu_counter_init(&sbi->s_dirtyclusters_counter, 0,
4333 GFP_KERNEL);
4334 if (!err)
4335 err = percpu_init_rwsem(&sbi->s_journal_flag_rwsem);
4336
4337 if (err) {
4338 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "insufficient memory");
4339 goto failed_mount6;
4340 }
4341
4342 if (ext4_has_feature_flex_bg(sb))
4343 if (!ext4_fill_flex_info(sb)) {
4344 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
4345 "unable to initialize "
4346 "flex_bg meta info!");
4347 goto failed_mount6;
4348 }
4349
4350 err = ext4_register_li_request(sb, first_not_zeroed);
4351 if (err)
4352 goto failed_mount6;
4353
4354 err = ext4_register_sysfs(sb);
4355 if (err)
4356 goto failed_mount7;
4357
4358#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
4359 /* Enable quota usage during mount. */
4360 if (ext4_has_feature_quota(sb) && !sb_rdonly(sb)) {
4361 err = ext4_enable_quotas(sb);
4362 if (err)
4363 goto failed_mount8;
4364 }
4365#endif /* CONFIG_QUOTA */
4366
4367 EXT4_SB(sb)->s_mount_state |= EXT4_ORPHAN_FS;
4368 ext4_orphan_cleanup(sb, es);
4369 EXT4_SB(sb)->s_mount_state &= ~EXT4_ORPHAN_FS;
4370 if (needs_recovery) {
4371 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "recovery complete");
4372 ext4_mark_recovery_complete(sb, es);
4373 }
4374 if (EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal) {
4375 if (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS) == EXT4_MOUNT_JOURNAL_DATA)
4376 descr = " journalled data mode";
4377 else if (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS) == EXT4_MOUNT_ORDERED_DATA)
4378 descr = " ordered data mode";
4379 else
4380 descr = " writeback data mode";
4381 } else
4382 descr = "out journal";
4383
4384 if (test_opt(sb, DISCARD)) {
4385 struct request_queue *q = bdev_get_queue(sb->s_bdev);
4386 if (!blk_queue_discard(q))
4387 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING,
4388 "mounting with \"discard\" option, but "
4389 "the device does not support discard");
4390 }
4391
4392 if (___ratelimit(&ext4_mount_msg_ratelimit, "EXT4-fs mount"))
4393 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "mounted filesystem with%s. "
4394 "Opts: %.*s%s%s", descr,
4395 (int) sizeof(sbi->s_es->s_mount_opts),
4396 sbi->s_es->s_mount_opts,
4397 *sbi->s_es->s_mount_opts ? "; " : "", orig_data);
4398
4399 if (es->s_error_count)
4400 mod_timer(&sbi->s_err_report, jiffies + 300*HZ); /* 5 minutes */
4401
4402 /* Enable message ratelimiting. Default is 10 messages per 5 secs. */
4403 ratelimit_state_init(&sbi->s_err_ratelimit_state, 5 * HZ, 10);
4404 ratelimit_state_init(&sbi->s_warning_ratelimit_state, 5 * HZ, 10);
4405 ratelimit_state_init(&sbi->s_msg_ratelimit_state, 5 * HZ, 10);
4406
4407 kfree(orig_data);
4408 return 0;
4409
4410cantfind_ext4:
4411 if (!silent)
4412 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "VFS: Can't find ext4 filesystem");
4413 goto failed_mount;
4414
4415#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
4416failed_mount8:
4417 ext4_unregister_sysfs(sb);
4418#endif
4419failed_mount7:
4420 ext4_unregister_li_request(sb);
4421failed_mount6:
4422 ext4_mb_release(sb);
4423 if (sbi->s_flex_groups)
4424 kvfree(sbi->s_flex_groups);
4425 percpu_counter_destroy(&sbi->s_freeclusters_counter);
4426 percpu_counter_destroy(&sbi->s_freeinodes_counter);
4427 percpu_counter_destroy(&sbi->s_dirs_counter);
4428 percpu_counter_destroy(&sbi->s_dirtyclusters_counter);
4429failed_mount5:
4430 ext4_ext_release(sb);
4431 ext4_release_system_zone(sb);
4432failed_mount4a:
4433 dput(sb->s_root);
4434 sb->s_root = NULL;
4435failed_mount4:
4436 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "mount failed");
4437 if (EXT4_SB(sb)->rsv_conversion_wq)
4438 destroy_workqueue(EXT4_SB(sb)->rsv_conversion_wq);
4439failed_mount_wq:
4440 if (sbi->s_ea_inode_cache) {
4441 ext4_xattr_destroy_cache(sbi->s_ea_inode_cache);
4442 sbi->s_ea_inode_cache = NULL;
4443 }
4444 if (sbi->s_ea_block_cache) {
4445 ext4_xattr_destroy_cache(sbi->s_ea_block_cache);
4446 sbi->s_ea_block_cache = NULL;
4447 }
4448 if (sbi->s_journal) {
4449 jbd2_journal_destroy(sbi->s_journal);
4450 sbi->s_journal = NULL;
4451 }
4452failed_mount3a:
4453 ext4_es_unregister_shrinker(sbi);
4454failed_mount3:
4455 del_timer_sync(&sbi->s_err_report);
4456 if (sbi->s_mmp_tsk)
4457 kthread_stop(sbi->s_mmp_tsk);
4458failed_mount2:
4459 for (i = 0; i < db_count; i++)
4460 brelse(sbi->s_group_desc[i]);
4461 kvfree(sbi->s_group_desc);
4462failed_mount:
4463 if (sbi->s_chksum_driver)
4464 crypto_free_shash(sbi->s_chksum_driver);
4465#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
4466 for (i = 0; i < EXT4_MAXQUOTAS; i++)
4467 kfree(sbi->s_qf_names[i]);
4468#endif
4469 ext4_blkdev_remove(sbi);
4470 brelse(bh);
4471out_fail:
4472 sb->s_fs_info = NULL;
4473 kfree(sbi->s_blockgroup_lock);
4474out_free_base:
4475 kfree(sbi);
4476 kfree(orig_data);
4477 fs_put_dax(dax_dev);
4478 return err ? err : ret;
4479}
4480
4481/*
4482 * Setup any per-fs journal parameters now. We'll do this both on
4483 * initial mount, once the journal has been initialised but before we've
4484 * done any recovery; and again on any subsequent remount.
4485 */
4486static void ext4_init_journal_params(struct super_block *sb, journal_t *journal)
4487{
4488 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
4489
4490 journal->j_commit_interval = sbi->s_commit_interval;
4491 journal->j_min_batch_time = sbi->s_min_batch_time;
4492 journal->j_max_batch_time = sbi->s_max_batch_time;
4493
4494 write_lock(&journal->j_state_lock);
4495 if (test_opt(sb, BARRIER))
4496 journal->j_flags |= JBD2_BARRIER;
4497 else
4498 journal->j_flags &= ~JBD2_BARRIER;
4499 if (test_opt(sb, DATA_ERR_ABORT))
4500 journal->j_flags |= JBD2_ABORT_ON_SYNCDATA_ERR;
4501 else
4502 journal->j_flags &= ~JBD2_ABORT_ON_SYNCDATA_ERR;
4503 write_unlock(&journal->j_state_lock);
4504}
4505
4506static struct inode *ext4_get_journal_inode(struct super_block *sb,
4507 unsigned int journal_inum)
4508{
4509 struct inode *journal_inode;
4510
4511 /*
4512 * Test for the existence of a valid inode on disk. Bad things
4513 * happen if we iget() an unused inode, as the subsequent iput()
4514 * will try to delete it.
4515 */
4516 journal_inode = ext4_iget(sb, journal_inum);
4517 if (IS_ERR(journal_inode)) {
4518 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "no journal found");
4519 return NULL;
4520 }
4521 if (!journal_inode->i_nlink) {
4522 make_bad_inode(journal_inode);
4523 iput(journal_inode);
4524 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "journal inode is deleted");
4525 return NULL;
4526 }
4527
4528 jbd_debug(2, "Journal inode found at %p: %lld bytes\n",
4529 journal_inode, journal_inode->i_size);
4530 if (!S_ISREG(journal_inode->i_mode)) {
4531 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "invalid journal inode");
4532 iput(journal_inode);
4533 return NULL;
4534 }
4535 return journal_inode;
4536}
4537
4538static journal_t *ext4_get_journal(struct super_block *sb,
4539 unsigned int journal_inum)
4540{
4541 struct inode *journal_inode;
4542 journal_t *journal;
4543
4544 BUG_ON(!ext4_has_feature_journal(sb));
4545
4546 journal_inode = ext4_get_journal_inode(sb, journal_inum);
4547 if (!journal_inode)
4548 return NULL;
4549
4550 journal = jbd2_journal_init_inode(journal_inode);
4551 if (!journal) {
4552 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "Could not load journal inode");
4553 iput(journal_inode);
4554 return NULL;
4555 }
4556 journal->j_private = sb;
4557 ext4_init_journal_params(sb, journal);
4558 return journal;
4559}
4560
4561static journal_t *ext4_get_dev_journal(struct super_block *sb,
4562 dev_t j_dev)
4563{
4564 struct buffer_head *bh;
4565 journal_t *journal;
4566 ext4_fsblk_t start;
4567 ext4_fsblk_t len;
4568 int hblock, blocksize;
4569 ext4_fsblk_t sb_block;
4570 unsigned long offset;
4571 struct ext4_super_block *es;
4572 struct block_device *bdev;
4573
4574 BUG_ON(!ext4_has_feature_journal(sb));
4575
4576 bdev = ext4_blkdev_get(j_dev, sb);
4577 if (bdev == NULL)
4578 return NULL;
4579
4580 blocksize = sb->s_blocksize;
4581 hblock = bdev_logical_block_size(bdev);
4582 if (blocksize < hblock) {
4583 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
4584 "blocksize too small for journal device");
4585 goto out_bdev;
4586 }
4587
4588 sb_block = EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE / blocksize;
4589 offset = EXT4_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE % blocksize;
4590 set_blocksize(bdev, blocksize);
4591 if (!(bh = __bread(bdev, sb_block, blocksize))) {
4592 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "couldn't read superblock of "
4593 "external journal");
4594 goto out_bdev;
4595 }
4596
4597 es = (struct ext4_super_block *) (bh->b_data + offset);
4598 if ((le16_to_cpu(es->s_magic) != EXT4_SUPER_MAGIC) ||
4599 !(le32_to_cpu(es->s_feature_incompat) &
4600 EXT4_FEATURE_INCOMPAT_JOURNAL_DEV)) {
4601 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "external journal has "
4602 "bad superblock");
4603 brelse(bh);
4604 goto out_bdev;
4605 }
4606
4607 if ((le32_to_cpu(es->s_feature_ro_compat) &
4608 EXT4_FEATURE_RO_COMPAT_METADATA_CSUM) &&
4609 es->s_checksum != ext4_superblock_csum(sb, es)) {
4610 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "external journal has "
4611 "corrupt superblock");
4612 brelse(bh);
4613 goto out_bdev;
4614 }
4615
4616 if (memcmp(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_journal_uuid, es->s_uuid, 16)) {
4617 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "journal UUID does not match");
4618 brelse(bh);
4619 goto out_bdev;
4620 }
4621
4622 len = ext4_blocks_count(es);
4623 start = sb_block + 1;
4624 brelse(bh); /* we're done with the superblock */
4625
4626 journal = jbd2_journal_init_dev(bdev, sb->s_bdev,
4627 start, len, blocksize);
4628 if (!journal) {
4629 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "failed to create device journal");
4630 goto out_bdev;
4631 }
4632 journal->j_private = sb;
4633 ll_rw_block(REQ_OP_READ, REQ_META | REQ_PRIO, 1, &journal->j_sb_buffer);
4634 wait_on_buffer(journal->j_sb_buffer);
4635 if (!buffer_uptodate(journal->j_sb_buffer)) {
4636 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "I/O error on journal device");
4637 goto out_journal;
4638 }
4639 if (be32_to_cpu(journal->j_superblock->s_nr_users) != 1) {
4640 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "External journal has more than one "
4641 "user (unsupported) - %d",
4642 be32_to_cpu(journal->j_superblock->s_nr_users));
4643 goto out_journal;
4644 }
4645 EXT4_SB(sb)->journal_bdev = bdev;
4646 ext4_init_journal_params(sb, journal);
4647 return journal;
4648
4649out_journal:
4650 jbd2_journal_destroy(journal);
4651out_bdev:
4652 ext4_blkdev_put(bdev);
4653 return NULL;
4654}
4655
4656static int ext4_load_journal(struct super_block *sb,
4657 struct ext4_super_block *es,
4658 unsigned long journal_devnum)
4659{
4660 journal_t *journal;
4661 unsigned int journal_inum = le32_to_cpu(es->s_journal_inum);
4662 dev_t journal_dev;
4663 int err = 0;
4664 int really_read_only;
4665
4666 BUG_ON(!ext4_has_feature_journal(sb));
4667
4668 if (journal_devnum &&
4669 journal_devnum != le32_to_cpu(es->s_journal_dev)) {
4670 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "external journal device major/minor "
4671 "numbers have changed");
4672 journal_dev = new_decode_dev(journal_devnum);
4673 } else
4674 journal_dev = new_decode_dev(le32_to_cpu(es->s_journal_dev));
4675
4676 really_read_only = bdev_read_only(sb->s_bdev);
4677
4678 /*
4679 * Are we loading a blank journal or performing recovery after a
4680 * crash? For recovery, we need to check in advance whether we
4681 * can get read-write access to the device.
4682 */
4683 if (ext4_has_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb)) {
4684 if (sb_rdonly(sb)) {
4685 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "INFO: recovery "
4686 "required on readonly filesystem");
4687 if (really_read_only) {
4688 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "write access "
4689 "unavailable, cannot proceed");
4690 return -EROFS;
4691 }
4692 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "write access will "
4693 "be enabled during recovery");
4694 }
4695 }
4696
4697 if (journal_inum && journal_dev) {
4698 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "filesystem has both journal "
4699 "and inode journals!");
4700 return -EINVAL;
4701 }
4702
4703 if (journal_inum) {
4704 if (!(journal = ext4_get_journal(sb, journal_inum)))
4705 return -EINVAL;
4706 } else {
4707 if (!(journal = ext4_get_dev_journal(sb, journal_dev)))
4708 return -EINVAL;
4709 }
4710
4711 if (!(journal->j_flags & JBD2_BARRIER))
4712 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "barriers disabled");
4713
4714 if (!ext4_has_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb))
4715 err = jbd2_journal_wipe(journal, !really_read_only);
4716 if (!err) {
4717 char *save = kmalloc(EXT4_S_ERR_LEN, GFP_KERNEL);
4718 if (save)
4719 memcpy(save, ((char *) es) +
4720 EXT4_S_ERR_START, EXT4_S_ERR_LEN);
4721 err = jbd2_journal_load(journal);
4722 if (save)
4723 memcpy(((char *) es) + EXT4_S_ERR_START,
4724 save, EXT4_S_ERR_LEN);
4725 kfree(save);
4726 }
4727
4728 if (err) {
4729 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "error loading journal");
4730 jbd2_journal_destroy(journal);
4731 return err;
4732 }
4733
4734 EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal = journal;
4735 ext4_clear_journal_err(sb, es);
4736
4737 if (!really_read_only && journal_devnum &&
4738 journal_devnum != le32_to_cpu(es->s_journal_dev)) {
4739 es->s_journal_dev = cpu_to_le32(journal_devnum);
4740
4741 /* Make sure we flush the recovery flag to disk. */
4742 ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
4743 }
4744
4745 return 0;
4746}
4747
4748static int ext4_commit_super(struct super_block *sb, int sync)
4749{
4750 struct ext4_super_block *es = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es;
4751 struct buffer_head *sbh = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_sbh;
4752 int error = 0;
4753
4754 if (!sbh || block_device_ejected(sb))
4755 return error;
4756
4757 /*
4758 * The superblock bh should be mapped, but it might not be if the
4759 * device was hot-removed. Not much we can do but fail the I/O.
4760 */
4761 if (!buffer_mapped(sbh))
4762 return error;
4763
4764 /*
4765 * If the file system is mounted read-only, don't update the
4766 * superblock write time. This avoids updating the superblock
4767 * write time when we are mounting the root file system
4768 * read/only but we need to replay the journal; at that point,
4769 * for people who are east of GMT and who make their clock
4770 * tick in localtime for Windows bug-for-bug compatibility,
4771 * the clock is set in the future, and this will cause e2fsck
4772 * to complain and force a full file system check.
4773 */
4774 if (!(sb->s_flags & MS_RDONLY))
4775 es->s_wtime = cpu_to_le32(get_seconds());
4776 if (sb->s_bdev->bd_part)
4777 es->s_kbytes_written =
4778 cpu_to_le64(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_kbytes_written +
4779 ((part_stat_read(sb->s_bdev->bd_part, sectors[1]) -
4780 EXT4_SB(sb)->s_sectors_written_start) >> 1));
4781 else
4782 es->s_kbytes_written =
4783 cpu_to_le64(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_kbytes_written);
4784 if (percpu_counter_initialized(&EXT4_SB(sb)->s_freeclusters_counter))
4785 ext4_free_blocks_count_set(es,
4786 EXT4_C2B(EXT4_SB(sb), percpu_counter_sum_positive(
4787 &EXT4_SB(sb)->s_freeclusters_counter)));
4788 if (percpu_counter_initialized(&EXT4_SB(sb)->s_freeinodes_counter))
4789 es->s_free_inodes_count =
4790 cpu_to_le32(percpu_counter_sum_positive(
4791 &EXT4_SB(sb)->s_freeinodes_counter));
4792 BUFFER_TRACE(sbh, "marking dirty");
4793 ext4_superblock_csum_set(sb);
4794 if (sync)
4795 lock_buffer(sbh);
4796 if (buffer_write_io_error(sbh)) {
4797 /*
4798 * Oh, dear. A previous attempt to write the
4799 * superblock failed. This could happen because the
4800 * USB device was yanked out. Or it could happen to
4801 * be a transient write error and maybe the block will
4802 * be remapped. Nothing we can do but to retry the
4803 * write and hope for the best.
4804 */
4805 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "previous I/O error to "
4806 "superblock detected");
4807 clear_buffer_write_io_error(sbh);
4808 set_buffer_uptodate(sbh);
4809 }
4810 mark_buffer_dirty(sbh);
4811 if (sync) {
4812 unlock_buffer(sbh);
4813 error = __sync_dirty_buffer(sbh,
4814 REQ_SYNC | (test_opt(sb, BARRIER) ? REQ_FUA : 0));
4815 if (error)
4816 return error;
4817
4818 error = buffer_write_io_error(sbh);
4819 if (error) {
4820 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "I/O error while writing "
4821 "superblock");
4822 clear_buffer_write_io_error(sbh);
4823 set_buffer_uptodate(sbh);
4824 }
4825 }
4826 return error;
4827}
4828
4829/*
4830 * Have we just finished recovery? If so, and if we are mounting (or
4831 * remounting) the filesystem readonly, then we will end up with a
4832 * consistent fs on disk. Record that fact.
4833 */
4834static void ext4_mark_recovery_complete(struct super_block *sb,
4835 struct ext4_super_block *es)
4836{
4837 journal_t *journal = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal;
4838
4839 if (!ext4_has_feature_journal(sb)) {
4840 BUG_ON(journal != NULL);
4841 return;
4842 }
4843 jbd2_journal_lock_updates(journal);
4844 if (jbd2_journal_flush(journal) < 0)
4845 goto out;
4846
4847 if (ext4_has_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb) && sb_rdonly(sb)) {
4848 ext4_clear_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb);
4849 ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
4850 }
4851
4852out:
4853 jbd2_journal_unlock_updates(journal);
4854}
4855
4856/*
4857 * If we are mounting (or read-write remounting) a filesystem whose journal
4858 * has recorded an error from a previous lifetime, move that error to the
4859 * main filesystem now.
4860 */
4861static void ext4_clear_journal_err(struct super_block *sb,
4862 struct ext4_super_block *es)
4863{
4864 journal_t *journal;
4865 int j_errno;
4866 const char *errstr;
4867
4868 BUG_ON(!ext4_has_feature_journal(sb));
4869
4870 journal = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal;
4871
4872 /*
4873 * Now check for any error status which may have been recorded in the
4874 * journal by a prior ext4_error() or ext4_abort()
4875 */
4876
4877 j_errno = jbd2_journal_errno(journal);
4878 if (j_errno) {
4879 char nbuf[16];
4880
4881 errstr = ext4_decode_error(sb, j_errno, nbuf);
4882 ext4_warning(sb, "Filesystem error recorded "
4883 "from previous mount: %s", errstr);
4884 ext4_warning(sb, "Marking fs in need of filesystem check.");
4885
4886 EXT4_SB(sb)->s_mount_state |= EXT4_ERROR_FS;
4887 es->s_state |= cpu_to_le16(EXT4_ERROR_FS);
4888 ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
4889
4890 jbd2_journal_clear_err(journal);
4891 jbd2_journal_update_sb_errno(journal);
4892 }
4893}
4894
4895/*
4896 * Force the running and committing transactions to commit,
4897 * and wait on the commit.
4898 */
4899int ext4_force_commit(struct super_block *sb)
4900{
4901 journal_t *journal;
4902
4903 if (sb_rdonly(sb))
4904 return 0;
4905
4906 journal = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal;
4907 return ext4_journal_force_commit(journal);
4908}
4909
4910static int ext4_sync_fs(struct super_block *sb, int wait)
4911{
4912 int ret = 0;
4913 tid_t target;
4914 bool needs_barrier = false;
4915 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
4916
4917 if (unlikely(ext4_forced_shutdown(EXT4_SB(sb))))
4918 return 0;
4919
4920 trace_ext4_sync_fs(sb, wait);
4921 flush_workqueue(sbi->rsv_conversion_wq);
4922 /*
4923 * Writeback quota in non-journalled quota case - journalled quota has
4924 * no dirty dquots
4925 */
4926 dquot_writeback_dquots(sb, -1);
4927 /*
4928 * Data writeback is possible w/o journal transaction, so barrier must
4929 * being sent at the end of the function. But we can skip it if
4930 * transaction_commit will do it for us.
4931 */
4932 if (sbi->s_journal) {
4933 target = jbd2_get_latest_transaction(sbi->s_journal);
4934 if (wait && sbi->s_journal->j_flags & JBD2_BARRIER &&
4935 !jbd2_trans_will_send_data_barrier(sbi->s_journal, target))
4936 needs_barrier = true;
4937
4938 if (jbd2_journal_start_commit(sbi->s_journal, &target)) {
4939 if (wait)
4940 ret = jbd2_log_wait_commit(sbi->s_journal,
4941 target);
4942 }
4943 } else if (wait && test_opt(sb, BARRIER))
4944 needs_barrier = true;
4945 if (needs_barrier) {
4946 int err;
4947 err = blkdev_issue_flush(sb->s_bdev, GFP_KERNEL, NULL);
4948 if (!ret)
4949 ret = err;
4950 }
4951
4952 return ret;
4953}
4954
4955/*
4956 * LVM calls this function before a (read-only) snapshot is created. This
4957 * gives us a chance to flush the journal completely and mark the fs clean.
4958 *
4959 * Note that only this function cannot bring a filesystem to be in a clean
4960 * state independently. It relies on upper layer to stop all data & metadata
4961 * modifications.
4962 */
4963static int ext4_freeze(struct super_block *sb)
4964{
4965 int error = 0;
4966 journal_t *journal;
4967
4968 if (sb_rdonly(sb))
4969 return 0;
4970
4971 journal = EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal;
4972
4973 if (journal) {
4974 /* Now we set up the journal barrier. */
4975 jbd2_journal_lock_updates(journal);
4976
4977 /*
4978 * Don't clear the needs_recovery flag if we failed to
4979 * flush the journal.
4980 */
4981 error = jbd2_journal_flush(journal);
4982 if (error < 0)
4983 goto out;
4984
4985 /* Journal blocked and flushed, clear needs_recovery flag. */
4986 ext4_clear_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb);
4987 }
4988
4989 error = ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
4990out:
4991 if (journal)
4992 /* we rely on upper layer to stop further updates */
4993 jbd2_journal_unlock_updates(journal);
4994 return error;
4995}
4996
4997/*
4998 * Called by LVM after the snapshot is done. We need to reset the RECOVER
4999 * flag here, even though the filesystem is not technically dirty yet.
5000 */
5001static int ext4_unfreeze(struct super_block *sb)
5002{
5003 if (sb_rdonly(sb) || ext4_forced_shutdown(EXT4_SB(sb)))
5004 return 0;
5005
5006 if (EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal) {
5007 /* Reset the needs_recovery flag before the fs is unlocked. */
5008 ext4_set_feature_journal_needs_recovery(sb);
5009 }
5010
5011 ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
5012 return 0;
5013}
5014
5015/*
5016 * Structure to save mount options for ext4_remount's benefit
5017 */
5018struct ext4_mount_options {
5019 unsigned long s_mount_opt;
5020 unsigned long s_mount_opt2;
5021 kuid_t s_resuid;
5022 kgid_t s_resgid;
5023 unsigned long s_commit_interval;
5024 u32 s_min_batch_time, s_max_batch_time;
5025#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5026 int s_jquota_fmt;
5027 char *s_qf_names[EXT4_MAXQUOTAS];
5028#endif
5029};
5030
5031static int ext4_remount(struct super_block *sb, int *flags, char *data)
5032{
5033 struct ext4_super_block *es;
5034 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
5035 unsigned long old_sb_flags;
5036 struct ext4_mount_options old_opts;
5037 int enable_quota = 0;
5038 ext4_group_t g;
5039 unsigned int journal_ioprio = DEFAULT_JOURNAL_IOPRIO;
5040 int err = 0;
5041#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5042 int i, j;
5043#endif
5044 char *orig_data = kstrdup(data, GFP_KERNEL);
5045
5046 /* Store the original options */
5047 old_sb_flags = sb->s_flags;
5048 old_opts.s_mount_opt = sbi->s_mount_opt;
5049 old_opts.s_mount_opt2 = sbi->s_mount_opt2;
5050 old_opts.s_resuid = sbi->s_resuid;
5051 old_opts.s_resgid = sbi->s_resgid;
5052 old_opts.s_commit_interval = sbi->s_commit_interval;
5053 old_opts.s_min_batch_time = sbi->s_min_batch_time;
5054 old_opts.s_max_batch_time = sbi->s_max_batch_time;
5055#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5056 old_opts.s_jquota_fmt = sbi->s_jquota_fmt;
5057 for (i = 0; i < EXT4_MAXQUOTAS; i++)
5058 if (sbi->s_qf_names[i]) {
5059 old_opts.s_qf_names[i] = kstrdup(sbi->s_qf_names[i],
5060 GFP_KERNEL);
5061 if (!old_opts.s_qf_names[i]) {
5062 for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
5063 kfree(old_opts.s_qf_names[j]);
5064 kfree(orig_data);
5065 return -ENOMEM;
5066 }
5067 } else
5068 old_opts.s_qf_names[i] = NULL;
5069#endif
5070 if (sbi->s_journal && sbi->s_journal->j_task->io_context)
5071 journal_ioprio = sbi->s_journal->j_task->io_context->ioprio;
5072
5073 if (!parse_options(data, sb, NULL, &journal_ioprio, 1)) {
5074 err = -EINVAL;
5075 goto restore_opts;
5076 }
5077
5078 if ((old_opts.s_mount_opt & EXT4_MOUNT_JOURNAL_CHECKSUM) ^
5079 test_opt(sb, JOURNAL_CHECKSUM)) {
5080 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "changing journal_checksum "
5081 "during remount not supported; ignoring");
5082 sbi->s_mount_opt ^= EXT4_MOUNT_JOURNAL_CHECKSUM;
5083 }
5084
5085 if (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS) == EXT4_MOUNT_JOURNAL_DATA) {
5086 if (test_opt2(sb, EXPLICIT_DELALLOC)) {
5087 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
5088 "both data=journal and delalloc");
5089 err = -EINVAL;
5090 goto restore_opts;
5091 }
5092 if (test_opt(sb, DIOREAD_NOLOCK)) {
5093 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
5094 "both data=journal and dioread_nolock");
5095 err = -EINVAL;
5096 goto restore_opts;
5097 }
5098 if (test_opt(sb, DAX)) {
5099 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
5100 "both data=journal and dax");
5101 err = -EINVAL;
5102 goto restore_opts;
5103 }
5104 } else if (test_opt(sb, DATA_FLAGS) == EXT4_MOUNT_ORDERED_DATA) {
5105 if (test_opt(sb, JOURNAL_ASYNC_COMMIT)) {
5106 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't mount with "
5107 "journal_async_commit in data=ordered mode");
5108 err = -EINVAL;
5109 goto restore_opts;
5110 }
5111 }
5112
5113 if ((sbi->s_mount_opt ^ old_opts.s_mount_opt) & EXT4_MOUNT_NO_MBCACHE) {
5114 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR, "can't enable nombcache during remount");
5115 err = -EINVAL;
5116 goto restore_opts;
5117 }
5118
5119 if ((sbi->s_mount_opt ^ old_opts.s_mount_opt) & EXT4_MOUNT_DAX) {
5120 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "warning: refusing change of "
5121 "dax flag with busy inodes while remounting");
5122 sbi->s_mount_opt ^= EXT4_MOUNT_DAX;
5123 }
5124
5125 if (sbi->s_mount_flags & EXT4_MF_FS_ABORTED)
5126 ext4_abort(sb, "Abort forced by user");
5127
5128 sb->s_flags = (sb->s_flags & ~MS_POSIXACL) |
5129 (test_opt(sb, POSIX_ACL) ? MS_POSIXACL : 0);
5130
5131 es = sbi->s_es;
5132
5133 if (sbi->s_journal) {
5134 ext4_init_journal_params(sb, sbi->s_journal);
5135 set_task_ioprio(sbi->s_journal->j_task, journal_ioprio);
5136 }
5137
5138 if (*flags & MS_LAZYTIME)
5139 sb->s_flags |= MS_LAZYTIME;
5140
5141 if ((bool)(*flags & MS_RDONLY) != sb_rdonly(sb)) {
5142 if (sbi->s_mount_flags & EXT4_MF_FS_ABORTED) {
5143 err = -EROFS;
5144 goto restore_opts;
5145 }
5146
5147 if (*flags & MS_RDONLY) {
5148 err = sync_filesystem(sb);
5149 if (err < 0)
5150 goto restore_opts;
5151 err = dquot_suspend(sb, -1);
5152 if (err < 0)
5153 goto restore_opts;
5154
5155 /*
5156 * First of all, the unconditional stuff we have to do
5157 * to disable replay of the journal when we next remount
5158 */
5159 sb->s_flags |= MS_RDONLY;
5160
5161 /*
5162 * OK, test if we are remounting a valid rw partition
5163 * readonly, and if so set the rdonly flag and then
5164 * mark the partition as valid again.
5165 */
5166 if (!(es->s_state & cpu_to_le16(EXT4_VALID_FS)) &&
5167 (sbi->s_mount_state & EXT4_VALID_FS))
5168 es->s_state = cpu_to_le16(sbi->s_mount_state);
5169
5170 if (sbi->s_journal)
5171 ext4_mark_recovery_complete(sb, es);
5172 } else {
5173 /* Make sure we can mount this feature set readwrite */
5174 if (ext4_has_feature_readonly(sb) ||
5175 !ext4_feature_set_ok(sb, 0)) {
5176 err = -EROFS;
5177 goto restore_opts;
5178 }
5179 /*
5180 * Make sure the group descriptor checksums
5181 * are sane. If they aren't, refuse to remount r/w.
5182 */
5183 for (g = 0; g < sbi->s_groups_count; g++) {
5184 struct ext4_group_desc *gdp =
5185 ext4_get_group_desc(sb, g, NULL);
5186
5187 if (!ext4_group_desc_csum_verify(sb, g, gdp)) {
5188 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_ERR,
5189 "ext4_remount: Checksum for group %u failed (%u!=%u)",
5190 g, le16_to_cpu(ext4_group_desc_csum(sb, g, gdp)),
5191 le16_to_cpu(gdp->bg_checksum));
5192 err = -EFSBADCRC;
5193 goto restore_opts;
5194 }
5195 }
5196
5197 /*
5198 * If we have an unprocessed orphan list hanging
5199 * around from a previously readonly bdev mount,
5200 * require a full umount/remount for now.
5201 */
5202 if (es->s_last_orphan) {
5203 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "Couldn't "
5204 "remount RDWR because of unprocessed "
5205 "orphan inode list. Please "
5206 "umount/remount instead");
5207 err = -EINVAL;
5208 goto restore_opts;
5209 }
5210
5211 /*
5212 * Mounting a RDONLY partition read-write, so reread
5213 * and store the current valid flag. (It may have
5214 * been changed by e2fsck since we originally mounted
5215 * the partition.)
5216 */
5217 if (sbi->s_journal)
5218 ext4_clear_journal_err(sb, es);
5219 sbi->s_mount_state = le16_to_cpu(es->s_state);
5220 if (!ext4_setup_super(sb, es, 0))
5221 sb->s_flags &= ~MS_RDONLY;
5222 if (ext4_has_feature_mmp(sb))
5223 if (ext4_multi_mount_protect(sb,
5224 le64_to_cpu(es->s_mmp_block))) {
5225 err = -EROFS;
5226 goto restore_opts;
5227 }
5228 enable_quota = 1;
5229 }
5230 }
5231
5232 /*
5233 * Reinitialize lazy itable initialization thread based on
5234 * current settings
5235 */
5236 if (sb_rdonly(sb) || !test_opt(sb, INIT_INODE_TABLE))
5237 ext4_unregister_li_request(sb);
5238 else {
5239 ext4_group_t first_not_zeroed;
5240 first_not_zeroed = ext4_has_uninit_itable(sb);
5241 ext4_register_li_request(sb, first_not_zeroed);
5242 }
5243
5244 ext4_setup_system_zone(sb);
5245 if (sbi->s_journal == NULL && !(old_sb_flags & MS_RDONLY))
5246 ext4_commit_super(sb, 1);
5247
5248#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5249 /* Release old quota file names */
5250 for (i = 0; i < EXT4_MAXQUOTAS; i++)
5251 kfree(old_opts.s_qf_names[i]);
5252 if (enable_quota) {
5253 if (sb_any_quota_suspended(sb))
5254 dquot_resume(sb, -1);
5255 else if (ext4_has_feature_quota(sb)) {
5256 err = ext4_enable_quotas(sb);
5257 if (err)
5258 goto restore_opts;
5259 }
5260 }
5261#endif
5262
5263 *flags = (*flags & ~MS_LAZYTIME) | (sb->s_flags & MS_LAZYTIME);
5264 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_INFO, "re-mounted. Opts: %s", orig_data);
5265 kfree(orig_data);
5266 return 0;
5267
5268restore_opts:
5269 sb->s_flags = old_sb_flags;
5270 sbi->s_mount_opt = old_opts.s_mount_opt;
5271 sbi->s_mount_opt2 = old_opts.s_mount_opt2;
5272 sbi->s_resuid = old_opts.s_resuid;
5273 sbi->s_resgid = old_opts.s_resgid;
5274 sbi->s_commit_interval = old_opts.s_commit_interval;
5275 sbi->s_min_batch_time = old_opts.s_min_batch_time;
5276 sbi->s_max_batch_time = old_opts.s_max_batch_time;
5277#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5278 sbi->s_jquota_fmt = old_opts.s_jquota_fmt;
5279 for (i = 0; i < EXT4_MAXQUOTAS; i++) {
5280 kfree(sbi->s_qf_names[i]);
5281 sbi->s_qf_names[i] = old_opts.s_qf_names[i];
5282 }
5283#endif
5284 kfree(orig_data);
5285 return err;
5286}

5288#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5289static int ext4_statfs_project(struct super_block *sb,
5290 kprojid_t projid, struct kstatfs *buf)
5291{
5292 struct kqid qid;
5293 struct dquot *dquot;
5294 u64 limit;
5295 u64 curblock;
5296
5297 qid = make_kqid_projid(projid);
5298 dquot = dqget(sb, qid);
5299 if (IS_ERR(dquot))
5300 return PTR_ERR(dquot);
5301 spin_lock(&dquot->dq_dqb_lock);
5302
5303 limit = (dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_bsoftlimit ?
5304 dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_bsoftlimit :
5305 dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_bhardlimit) >> sb->s_blocksize_bits;
5306 if (limit && buf->f_blocks > limit) {
5307 curblock = dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_curspace >> sb->s_blocksize_bits;
5308 buf->f_blocks = limit;
5309 buf->f_bfree = buf->f_bavail =
5310 (buf->f_blocks > curblock) ?
5311 (buf->f_blocks - curblock) : 0;
5312 }
5313
5314 limit = dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_isoftlimit ?
5315 dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_isoftlimit :
5316 dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_ihardlimit;
5317 if (limit && buf->f_files > limit) {
5318 buf->f_files = limit;
5319 buf->f_ffree =
5320 (buf->f_files > dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_curinodes) ?
5321 (buf->f_files - dquot->dq_dqb.dqb_curinodes) : 0;
5322 }
5323
5324 spin_unlock(&dquot->dq_dqb_lock);
5325 dqput(dquot);
5326 return 0;
5327}
5328#endif
5329
5330static int ext4_statfs(struct dentry *dentry, struct kstatfs *buf)
5331{
5332 struct super_block *sb = dentry->d_sb;
5333 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
5334 struct ext4_super_block *es = sbi->s_es;
5335 ext4_fsblk_t overhead = 0, resv_blocks;
5336 u64 fsid;
5337 s64 bfree;
5338 resv_blocks = EXT4_C2B(sbi, atomic64_read(&sbi->s_resv_clusters));
5339
5340 if (!test_opt(sb, MINIX_DF))
5341 overhead = sbi->s_overhead;
5342
5343 buf->f_type = EXT4_SUPER_MAGIC;
5344 buf->f_bsize = sb->s_blocksize;
5345 buf->f_blocks = ext4_blocks_count(es) - EXT4_C2B(sbi, overhead);
5346 bfree = percpu_counter_sum_positive(&sbi->s_freeclusters_counter) -
5347 percpu_counter_sum_positive(&sbi->s_dirtyclusters_counter);
5348 /* prevent underflow in case that few free space is available */
5349 buf->f_bfree = EXT4_C2B(sbi, max_t(s64, bfree, 0));
5350 buf->f_bavail = buf->f_bfree -
5351 (ext4_r_blocks_count(es) + resv_blocks);
5352 if (buf->f_bfree < (ext4_r_blocks_count(es) + resv_blocks))
5353 buf->f_bavail = 0;
5354 buf->f_files = le32_to_cpu(es->s_inodes_count);
5355 buf->f_ffree = percpu_counter_sum_positive(&sbi->s_freeinodes_counter);
5356 buf->f_namelen = EXT4_NAME_LEN;
5357 fsid = le64_to_cpup((void *)es->s_uuid) ^
5358 le64_to_cpup((void *)es->s_uuid + sizeof(u64));
5359 buf->f_fsid.val[0] = fsid & 0xFFFFFFFFUL;
5360 buf->f_fsid.val[1] = (fsid >> 32) & 0xFFFFFFFFUL;
5361
5362#ifdef CONFIG_QUOTA
5363 if (ext4_test_inode_flag(dentry->d_inode, EXT4_INODE_PROJINHERIT) &&
5364 sb_has_quota_limits_enabled(sb, PRJQUOTA))
5365 ext4_statfs_project(sb, EXT4_I(dentry->d_inode)->i_projid, buf);
5366#endif
5367 return 0;
5368}
