5489
5490/*
5491 * Standard function to be called on quota_on
5492 */
5493static int ext4_quota_on(struct super_block *sb, int type, int format_id,
5494 const struct path *path)
5495{
5496 int err;
5497
5498 if (!test_opt(sb, QUOTA))
5499 return -EINVAL;
5500
5501 /* Quotafile not on the same filesystem? */
5502 if (path->dentry->d_sb != sb)
5503 return -EXDEV;
5504 /* Journaling quota? */
5505 if (EXT4_SB(sb)->s_qf_names[type]) {
5506 /* Quotafile not in fs root? */
5507 if (path->dentry->d_parent != sb->s_root)
5508 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING,
5509 "Quota file not on filesystem root. "
5510 "Journaled quota will not work");
5511 sb_dqopt(sb)->flags |= DQUOT_NOLIST_DIRTY;
5512 } else {
5513 /*
5514 * Clear the flag just in case mount options changed since
5515 * last time.
5516 */
5517 sb_dqopt(sb)->flags &= ~DQUOT_NOLIST_DIRTY;
5518 }
5519
5520 /*
5521 * When we journal data on quota file, we have to flush journal to see
5522 * all updates to the file when we bypass pagecache...
5523 */
5524 if (EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal &&
5525 ext4_should_journal_data(d_inode(path->dentry))) {
5526 /*
5527 * We don't need to lock updates but journal_flush() could
5528 * otherwise be livelocked...
5529 */
5530 jbd2_journal_lock_updates(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal);
5531 err = jbd2_journal_flush(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal);
5532 jbd2_journal_unlock_updates(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal);
5533 if (err)
5534 return err;
5535 }
5536
5537 lockdep_set_quota_inode(path->dentry->d_inode, I_DATA_SEM_QUOTA);
5538 err = dquot_quota_on(sb, type, format_id, path);
5539 if (err) {
5540 lockdep_set_quota_inode(path->dentry->d_inode,
5541 I_DATA_SEM_NORMAL);
5542 } else {
5543 struct inode *inode = d_inode(path->dentry);
5544 handle_t *handle;
5545
5546 /*
5547 * Set inode flags to prevent userspace from messing with quota
5548 * files. If this fails, we return success anyway since quotas
5549 * are already enabled and this is not a hard failure.
5550 */
5551 inode_lock(inode);
5552 handle = ext4_journal_start(inode, EXT4_HT_QUOTA, 1);
5553 if (IS_ERR(handle))
5554 goto unlock_inode;
5555 EXT4_I(inode)->i_flags |= EXT4_NOATIME_FL | EXT4_IMMUTABLE_FL;
5556 inode_set_flags(inode, S_NOATIME | S_IMMUTABLE,
5557 S_NOATIME | S_IMMUTABLE);
5558 ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
5559 ext4_journal_stop(handle);
5560 unlock_inode:
5561 inode_unlock(inode);
5562 }
5563 return err;
5564}
5565
5566static int ext4_quota_enable(struct super_block *sb, int type, int format_id,
5567 unsigned int flags)
5568{
5569 int err;
5570 struct inode *qf_inode;
5571 unsigned long qf_inums[EXT4_MAXQUOTAS] = {
5572 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_usr_quota_inum),
5573 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_grp_quota_inum),
5574 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_prj_quota_inum)
5575 };
5576
5577 BUG_ON(!ext4_has_feature_quota(sb));
5578
5579 if (!qf_inums[type])
5580 return -EPERM;
5581
5582 qf_inode = ext4_iget(sb, qf_inums[type]);
5583 if (IS_ERR(qf_inode)) {
5584 ext4_error(sb, "Bad quota inode # %lu", qf_inums[type]);
5585 return PTR_ERR(qf_inode);
5586 }
5587
5588 /* Don't account quota for quota files to avoid recursion */
5589 qf_inode->i_flags |= S_NOQUOTA;
5590 lockdep_set_quota_inode(qf_inode, I_DATA_SEM_QUOTA);
5591 err = dquot_enable(qf_inode, type, format_id, flags);
5592 iput(qf_inode);
5593 if (err)
5594 lockdep_set_quota_inode(qf_inode, I_DATA_SEM_NORMAL);
5595
5596 return err;
5597}
5598
5599/* Enable usage tracking for all quota types. */
5600static int ext4_enable_quotas(struct super_block *sb)
5601{
5602 int type, err = 0;
5603 unsigned long qf_inums[EXT4_MAXQUOTAS] = {
5604 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_usr_quota_inum),
5605 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_grp_quota_inum),
5606 le32_to_cpu(EXT4_SB(sb)->s_es->s_prj_quota_inum)
5607 };
5608 bool quota_mopt[EXT4_MAXQUOTAS] = {
5609 test_opt(sb, USRQUOTA),
5610 test_opt(sb, GRPQUOTA),
5611 test_opt(sb, PRJQUOTA),
5612 };
5613
5614 sb_dqopt(sb)->flags |= DQUOT_QUOTA_SYS_FILE | DQUOT_NOLIST_DIRTY;
5615 for (type = 0; type < EXT4_MAXQUOTAS; type++) {
5616 if (qf_inums[type]) {
5617 err = ext4_quota_enable(sb, type, QFMT_VFS_V1,
5618 DQUOT_USAGE_ENABLED |
5619 (quota_mopt[type] ? DQUOT_LIMITS_ENABLED : 0));
5620 if (err) {
5621 for (type--; type >= 0; type--)
5622 dquot_quota_off(sb, type);
5623
5624 ext4_warning(sb,
5625 "Failed to enable quota tracking "
5626 "(type=%d, err=%d). Please run "
5627 "e2fsck to fix.", type, err);
5628 return err;
5629 }
5630 }
5631 }
5632 return 0;
5633}
5634
5635static int ext4_quota_off(struct super_block *sb, int type)
5636{
5637 struct inode *inode = sb_dqopt(sb)->files[type];
5638 handle_t *handle;
5639 int err;
5640
5641 /* Force all delayed allocation blocks to be allocated.
5642 * Caller already holds s_umount sem */
5643 if (test_opt(sb, DELALLOC))
5644 sync_filesystem(sb);
5645
5646 if (!inode || !igrab(inode))
5647 goto out;
5648
5649 err = dquot_quota_off(sb, type);
5650 if (err || ext4_has_feature_quota(sb))
5651 goto out_put;
5652
5653 inode_lock(inode);
5654 /*
5655 * Update modification times of quota files when userspace can
5656 * start looking at them. If we fail, we return success anyway since
5657 * this is not a hard failure and quotas are already disabled.
5658 */
5659 handle = ext4_journal_start(inode, EXT4_HT_QUOTA, 1);
5660 if (IS_ERR(handle))
5661 goto out_unlock;
5662 EXT4_I(inode)->i_flags &= ~(EXT4_NOATIME_FL | EXT4_IMMUTABLE_FL);
5663 inode_set_flags(inode, 0, S_NOATIME | S_IMMUTABLE);
5664 inode->i_mtime = inode->i_ctime = current_time(inode);
5665 ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
5666 ext4_journal_stop(handle);
5667out_unlock:
5668 inode_unlock(inode);
5669out_put:
5670 lockdep_set_quota_inode(inode, I_DATA_SEM_NORMAL);
5671 iput(inode);
5672 return err;
5673out:
5674 return dquot_quota_off(sb, type);
5675}
5676
5677/* Read data from quotafile - avoid pagecache and such because we cannot afford
5678 * acquiring the locks... As quota files are never truncated and quota code
5679 * itself serializes the operations (and no one else should touch the files)
5680 * we don't have to be afraid of races */
5681static ssize_t ext4_quota_read(struct super_block *sb, int type, char *data,
5682 size_t len, loff_t off)
5683{
5684 struct inode *inode = sb_dqopt(sb)->files[type];
5685 ext4_lblk_t blk = off >> EXT4_BLOCK_SIZE_BITS(sb);
5686 int offset = off & (sb->s_blocksize - 1);
5687 int tocopy;
5688 size_t toread;
5689 struct buffer_head *bh;
5690 loff_t i_size = i_size_read(inode);
5691
5692 if (off > i_size)
5693 return 0;
5694 if (off+len > i_size)
5695 len = i_size-off;
5696 toread = len;
5697 while (toread > 0) {
5698 tocopy = sb->s_blocksize - offset < toread ?
5699 sb->s_blocksize - offset : toread;
5700 bh = ext4_bread(NULL, inode, blk, 0);
5701 if (IS_ERR(bh))
5702 return PTR_ERR(bh);
5703 if (!bh) /* A hole? */
5704 memset(data, 0, tocopy);
5705 else
5706 memcpy(data, bh->b_data+offset, tocopy);
5707 brelse(bh);
5708 offset = 0;
5709 toread -= tocopy;
5710 data += tocopy;
5711 blk++;
5712 }
5713 return len;
5714}
5715
5716/* Write to quotafile (we know the transaction is already started and has
5717 * enough credits) */
5718static ssize_t ext4_quota_write(struct super_block *sb, int type,
5719 const char *data, size_t len, loff_t off)
5720{
5721 struct inode *inode = sb_dqopt(sb)->files[type];
5722 ext4_lblk_t blk = off >> EXT4_BLOCK_SIZE_BITS(sb);
5723 int err, offset = off & (sb->s_blocksize - 1);
5724 int retries = 0;
5725 struct buffer_head *bh;
5726 handle_t *handle = journal_current_handle();
5727
5728 if (EXT4_SB(sb)->s_journal && !handle) {
5729 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "Quota write (off=%llu, len=%llu)"
5730 " cancelled because transaction is not started",
5731 (unsigned long long)off, (unsigned long long)len);
5732 return -EIO;
5733 }
5734 /*
5735 * Since we account only one data block in transaction credits,
5736 * then it is impossible to cross a block boundary.
5737 */
5738 if (sb->s_blocksize - offset < len) {
5739 ext4_msg(sb, KERN_WARNING, "Quota write (off=%llu, len=%llu)"
5740 " cancelled because not block aligned",
5741 (unsigned long long)off, (unsigned long long)len);
5742 return -EIO;
5743 }
5744
5745 do {
5746 bh = ext4_bread(handle, inode, blk,
5747 EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CREATE |
5748 EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_METADATA_NOFAIL);
5749 } while (IS_ERR(bh) && (PTR_ERR(bh) == -ENOSPC) &&
5750 ext4_should_retry_alloc(inode->i_sb, &retries));
5751 if (IS_ERR(bh))
5752 return PTR_ERR(bh);
5753 if (!bh)
5754 goto out;
5755 BUFFER_TRACE(bh, "get write access");
5756 err = ext4_journal_get_write_access(handle, bh);
5757 if (err) {
5758 brelse(bh);
5759 return err;
5760 }
5761 lock_buffer(bh);
5762 memcpy(bh->b_data+offset, data, len);
5763 flush_dcache_page(bh->b_page);
5764 unlock_buffer(bh);
5765 err = ext4_handle_dirty_metadata(handle, NULL, bh);
5766 brelse(bh);
5767out:
5768 if (inode->i_size < off + len) {
5769 i_size_write(inode, off + len);
5770 EXT4_I(inode)->i_disksize = inode->i_size;
5771 ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
5772 }
5773 return len;
5774}
5775
5776static int ext4_get_next_id(struct super_block *sb, struct kqid *qid)
5777{
5778 const struct quota_format_ops *ops;
5779
5780 if (!sb_has_quota_loaded(sb, qid->type))
5781 return -ESRCH;
5782 ops = sb_dqopt(sb)->ops[qid->type];
5783 if (!ops || !ops->get_next_id)
5784 return -ENOSYS;
5785 return dquot_get_next_id(sb, qid);
5786}
5787#endif

5790 const char *dev_name, void *data)
5791{
5792 return mount_bdev(fs_type, flags, dev_name, data, ext4_fill_super);
5793}

5838static inline int ext3_feature_set_ok(struct super_block *sb)
5839{

5860/* Shared across all ext4 file systems */
5861wait_queue_head_t ext4__ioend_wq[EXT4_WQ_HASH_SZ];
5862
5863static int __init ext4_init_fs(void)
5864{
5865 int i, err;
5866
5867 ratelimit_state_init(&ext4_mount_msg_ratelimit, 30 * HZ, 64);
5868 ext4_li_info = NULL;
5869 mutex_init(&ext4_li_mtx);
5870
5871 /* Build-time check for flags consistency */
5872 ext4_check_flag_values();
5873
5874 for (i = 0; i < EXT4_WQ_HASH_SZ; i++)
5875 init_waitqueue_head(&ext4__ioend_wq[i]);
5876
5877 err = ext4_init_es();
5878 if (err)
5879 return err;
5880
5881 err = ext4_init_pageio();
5882 if (err)
5883 goto out5;
5884
5885 err = ext4_init_system_zone();
5886 if (err)
5887 goto out4;
5888
5889 err = ext4_init_sysfs();
5890 if (err)
5891 goto out3;
5892
5893 err = ext4_init_mballoc();
5894 if (err)
5895 goto out2;
5896 err = init_inodecache();
5897 if (err)
5898 goto out1;
5899 register_as_ext3();
5900 register_as_ext2();
5901 err = register_filesystem(&ext4_fs_type);
5902 if (err)
5903 goto out;
5904
5905 return 0;
5906out:
5907 unregister_as_ext2();
5908 unregister_as_ext3();
5909 destroy_inodecache();
5910out1:
5911 ext4_exit_mballoc();
5912out2:
5913 ext4_exit_sysfs();
5914out3:
5915 ext4_exit_system_zone();
5916out4:
5917 ext4_exit_pageio();
5918out5:
5919 ext4_exit_es();
5920
5921 return err;
5922}

5924static void __exit ext4_exit_fs(void)
5925{
5926 ext4_destroy_lazyinit_thread();
5927 unregister_as_ext2();
5928 unregister_as_ext3();
5929 unregister_filesystem(&ext4_fs_type);
5930 destroy_inodecache();
5931 ext4_exit_mballoc();
5932 ext4_exit_sysfs();
5933 ext4_exit_system_zone();
5934 ext4_exit_pageio();
5935 ext4_exit_es();
5936}
